title: spinach bread
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan in oven. Combine remaining ingredients, adding cheese and spinach last.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes. Cool 1/2 hour before serving.
May be put on a hot tray as an hors d'oeuvre.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: spicy sausage and peppers
directions: Cut sausage into 1/2-inch lengths.
Cut peppers into long 1/2-inch strips and cook in boiling water 1 1/2 minutes; drain. Rinse with cold water and set aside.
Halve onion and cut each half into 8 wedges; put aside.

title: garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes in 2-inch chunks.
Place in large pot of cold water.
Bring to boil for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheeses
, reserving 1/2 can sauce for top.
Pat out in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cheeses, saving small amount for topping.
Put cheese mixture in center of meat and fold to make a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in uncovered pan.
Remove.
Sprinkle sauce and cheese on top of loaf and bake for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: norwegian sweet soup
directions: Add tapioca to boiling water, stirring frequently.
Add rest of ingredients except grape juice and boil until fruit is tender. When soup is done, add grape juice.
Serve with Rusks.
May be served cold as dessert.
Garnish with whipped cream and chopped nuts.

title: pistachio pie
directions: If pie crust must be baked, set aside until cooled.
Make 2 boxes of pudding, using the milk.
Pour pudding into cooled pie shell.
Serve with whipped cream.
Garnish with shaved chocolate or maraschino cherries.

title: ginger creams
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Dissolve soda in hot water. Stir in dry ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon about 2 inches apart. Bake about 8 minutes.
Frost with confectioners sugar icing.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam before putting cookies on.

title: zesty squash
directions: Place margarine and garlic in 2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, until melted.
Stir in oregano, basil, salt and pepper.
Add zucchini and toss to coat.
Cover and microwave on High until squash is tender (about 8 to 10 minutes), stirring halfway through cooking time.
Stir in tomato, cover and let stand 2 minutes.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat peanut butter, brown sugar and vanilla together.
Gradually add milk, beating until smooth.
Add to flour mixture, blending just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until casserole is firm.

title: sweet pie dough
directions: Mix ingredients to form dough.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. For small syrup pie, bake at 300°.

title: peanut butter fantasy fudge
directions: Stir together margarine, sugar and evaporated milk in heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly. Boil 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 235°.
Stir constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, then add remaining ingredients and mix until well blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into small squares.

title: betty wright's hot dog sauce
directions: Simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
May be reheated several times.
Good as a snack with corn chips.

title: family recipe buttermilk biscuits
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the flour, soda, sugar, and salt.
Dissolve the yeast in the lukewarm water.
Add the yeast mixture, shortening, and buttermilk to the flour mixture.
Mix together well.
Cover and let rise.
Knead just a little. Refrigerate overnight.

title: tamale pie
directions: Saute onions and garlic in large pan.
Add meat and brown.
Add salt, chili powder, tomato sauce, corn and olives.
Let simmer about 20 minutes.
Mix eggs, milk, corn meal, salt and 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in greased pan.

title: curry chicken
directions: Melt butter.
Saute onions until transparent.
Remove from heat.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Drain mushrooms (save liquid). Add water to mushroom liquid to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Gradually stir into flour mixture until smooth, then add the evaporated milk, curry and mushrooms.
Cook on medium heat until thick. Arrange meat and broccoli in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over meat and broccoli.
Add cheese and bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until bubbly around edges.

title: apple butter cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in 1 cup apple butter.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with sour milk.
(To make sour milk, measure 1 tablespoon lemon juice into measuring cup; add milk to make 1 cup and stir.)
Turn into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool. Spread bottom layer of cooled cake with 1/4 cup apple butter.
Top with fluffy frosting.
Cover top cake layer.
Frost sides and top. Swirl apple butter onto frosted top to give marbled effect.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix together and fry.
Delicious served with apple butter.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Line a jelly roll pan with aluminum foil.
Butter foil and set aside.
Combine first 4 ingredients in a heavy, 2-quart saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring gently until sugar dissolves.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes to wash down sugar crystals from the sides of the pan.
Uncover and cook to hard crack stage on candy thermometer.
Stir in butter, vanilla and soda.
Pour mixture onto buttered foil, spreading thinly.
Let cool and break into pieces.
Yields 3/4 pound.

title: burritos
directions: Cook roast and shred; mix in remaining ingredients and roll into flour tortillas.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Combine rhubarb, sugar and tapioca.
Set aside.
Beat eggs. Add milk and vanilla.
Pour egg mixture over rhubarb.
Blend well. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 minutes longer.
Spread with whipped topping before serving.

title: pumpkin ribbon pie
directions: In medium saucepan, mix gelatin with 1/2 cup sugar.
Blend in egg yolks beaten with milk.
Let stand 1 minute. Stir over low heat until gelatin is completely dissolved, about 5 minutes. Add vanilla.

title: grammie bray's boiled cake
directions: Put all together (except flour, soda and vanilla) in a saucepan and boil 10 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Add flour, soda and vanilla.
Add nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice mix according to package directions, substituting chicken broth for water.
Let cool.
Add celery, green onion, water chestnuts, mushrooms, butter and soy sauce.
Mix all together.
Place in a casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until hot.

title: italian macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and place in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and toss gently.
Turn into a 2 1/2-quart casserole greased with 1 teaspoon butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: tangy swirled biscuits
directions: Mix cream cheese with jello; set aside.
Mix ingredients.
Turn dough on floured surface, knead 10 times.
Roll out dough like pie crust, 12 x 10-inches.
Spread jello mixture over dough.
Roll like a jelly roll.
Pinch ends to seal.
Cut into 12 (1-inch) slices. Arrange in greased pan.
Bake until brown, 15 to 20 minutes at 425°.

title: country chicken loaf
directions: Force chicken, carrots and peas through a food grinder.
Add remaining ingredients and place in greased loaf pan or ring mold. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes until firm.

title: honolulu coolers(alcoholic drink)
directions: Pour pineapple juice and Southern Comfort in equal parts or to taste into the blender with ice. Mix until ice is crushed, then serve.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add egg and milk.
Beat with wire whisk until smooth.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Combine cheese, tomatoes, chilies and onion in a saucepan. Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with chips. Makes about 6 cups.

title: sole amandine(4 servings)
directions: Rinse fish; pat dry.
In large skillet over high heat, cook almonds, stirring constantly to prevent burning, until lightly toasted, about 2 minutes.
Remove almonds; set aside.
Reduce heat to medium.
Add butter.
When bubbling, add fish and cook 1 to 2 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily with fork. Transfer to a platter.
Sprinkle with lemon peel, lemon juice and white pepper.
Top with toasted almonds.

title: cape cod cranberry bread
directions: Mix flour with soda, baking powder, salt, and spices.
In another bowl, cream butter; gradually beat in sugar.
Add egg and beat until blended. Gradually beat in corn syrup and water.
Add flour mixture, beating until smooth.
Stir in cranberries and cereal; pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.

title: quick and easy cherry crunch
directions: Pour cherry pie filling into a 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle lemon juice over filling.
Sprinkle cake mix on top; drizzle with butter.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Brown sausage; add chopped onion, celery, bell pepper, parsley and green onions.
Add tomato paste and water.
Cook two hours. Add shrimp last 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: pizza pineapple dessert
directions: Roll out pastry to 15-inch circle. Center in lightly floured 12-inch pizza pan.
Turn edge toward center.

Press gently into base dough. Make diagonal cuts around edge with sharp knife. Brush edge with Egg Wash. Bake in preheated 425° oven for 10 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake 35 to 40 minutes. Remove from oven. Cool thoroughly. Transfer pastry shell carefully to serving plate. Spread Apricot Glaze generously over bottom of shell. Arrange pineapple rings over glaze with the cherries.

title: crunchy stuffing balls
directions: Saute onion and celery in fat until tender.
Add broken matzos and toast lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well. Add nuts.
Shape into 2-inch balls and bake at 375° for 20 minutes until brown.

title: caramel cocoa squares
directions: Melt the caramels with 1/3 cup of the evaporated milk.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: zucchini bread ring
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Set grated zucchini between paper towels and press to remove excess moisture.
In medium bowl, combine oats with flour, baking soda, cream of tartar, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice; mix well.
In separate bowl, combine honey, pineapple juice concentrate, vanilla, applesauce and crushed pineapple; stir into flour mixture.
Gently mix in egg whites. Stir in raisins and well drained, grated zucchini.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put cinnamon and 3/4 cup sugar in a plastic bag and shake biscuit pieces, which have been cut into quarter pieces.
Place them in a Bundt pan or a 13 x 9 x 2 pan.

title: jello jigglers
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin.
Dissolve completely, then pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Dip bottom of pan in warm water.
Cut Jigglers and remove.

title: best bean soup
directions: Place all ingredients in stock pot (except potatoes).
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Remove ham bone and remove all meat.
Cut in small pieces.
Add mashed potatoes to soup; bring to a boil.
Add ham and serve.

title: reese's tarts
directions: Cream butters and sugars thoroughly.
Add egg and vanilla. Beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture. Take rounded teaspoonful of dough and place in greased mini muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until cookie puffs up and is barely done.
Remove from oven and immediately push a peanut butter cup into each cookie center.
The cookies will deflate and form a tart shell around the peanut butter cup. Let cool in pan, then refrigerate until shine leaves the chocolate.
Gently lift each tart out with the tip of a sharp knife.

title: boiled raisin cake
directions: Cover raisins with boiling water.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Cool. Set aside.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine ingredients and serve with your favorite vegetables.

title: taco salad
directions: Layer ingredients in salad bowl.
At last minute, pour entire bottle of dressing over top of salad.
Do not substitute any other dressing or it will diminish flavors.

title: thai chicken salad
directions: Slice chicken thighs thinly.
Marinate in mixture.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.
Cook enough rice for 4 to 6 servings.
Chop (julienne) some carrots, sliced cucumber and scallions or red onion.
Pour chicken mixture over rice.
Garnish with vegetables and cilantro.

title: phil's candy
directions: Mix together.
Roll into small balls, refrigerate 1 hour or so, then eat.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Trim ends off squash; do not peel squash.
Spray thin layer of Pam or other oil on bottom of dish.
Layer first with cross-cut zucchini slices, then layer of tomato slices, followed by onion slices.
Snip fresh basil (or dried) over top.
Cover with cracker crumbs, followed by Cheddar cheese.
Bake, covered, in 350°
oven. Take cover off last 5 to 10 minutes, if desired, to brown top. Use equal amounts of vegetables cut same thickness, 1/2-inch.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle rice in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine soup and water.
Pour over rice.
Place chicken pieces, skin side up, on rice.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place butter pieces on each piece of chicken.
Bake for 1 hour. Yields 6 servings.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Peel and thinly slice onions.
Place in a shallow microwave safe dish; dot with margarine.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on high for 3 minutes.
Stir and microwave on high an additional 5 to 7 minutes.
Remove from oven, stir in cheese, pepper and salt.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Top with cracker crumbs, serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar.
Place dry ingredients into a large bowl and make a well in the center.
Place strawberries with juice, eggs, oil and pecans in the well.
Stir until all ingredients are moistened.
Pour into two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans that have been well greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Check at 60 minutes.
Cool in pan for 30 minutes; turn out onto cooling racks.
Freeze well, if needed to keep.

title: tropical storm
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container.
Cover; blend on medium speed about 1 minute or until ice is finely crushed.

title: garlicky baked tomatoes
directions: Preparation time:
10 minutes; cooking time:
15 minutes. Make-ahead tip:
The tomatoes can be prepared through the step where you spread the cheese on them up to 2 hours before baking.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute onion in oil until tender.
Add meat; cook until brown. Drain excess fat.
Add garlic salt, oregano, salt, pepper and pizza sauce.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese with beaten eggs.
Place in layers lasagna noodles, meat sauce, cottage cheese mixture and cheese.
Put in 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: starter for sourdough bread
directions: In a small saucepan, heat 1 cup milk until it reaches 98°. Remove from heat and stir in 3 tablespoons unflavored yogurt.
Pour into glass jar or nonmetal bowl.
Cover airtight and set in a warm spot.

title: hot or cold turkey loaf
directions: Lightly mix all ingredients and mold into loaf.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours. Makes 8 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer in order in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Heat the above until smooth.
Add cocktail wieners and heat. Keep Warm.

title: cheesy chicken crescent supper
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl combine chicken and 2 Tbsp. cheese.
Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles.
Place 2 Tbsp. chicken mixture on each roll, then roll up in a ball.
In a medium sauce pan combine soup, milk, and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Pour 1/2 soup mix into an 8 x 8 baking dish. Arrange rolls on hot soup.
Pour remaining soup over rolls.
Bake 30 minutes or until chicken is cooked thoroughly.
Remove from oven, sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie dish.
Sprinkle meat and cheese in pie plate. Mix other ingredients on high for 1 minute. Pour in pie plate.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown and knife comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: You will need a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: beef foldovers
directions: Separate biscuits.
Pat each out on a floured surface to 5-inch circle.
Brown meat, onion, green pepper and oregano.
Place a heaping tablespoonful of meat mixture on biscuit circle.
Fold in half and seal edges with a fork.
Deep fat fry until golden brown. Drain on paper towel.
Makes 20 foldovers.

title: jam cake
directions: If you use self-rising flour, do not use soda and salt. Cream sugar and butter. Add sugar and butter. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one. Add flour, milk and spices and then jam. This will make 4 big layers. Bake at 350°.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Put 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish with the stick of butter in the oven and let butter melt and get hot at 350°.
While butter is getting hot, mix flour and sugar together in a bowl.
Add milk and mix.
When butter is hot, take out of oven and pour the flour mixture into the butter.
Add the can of fruit.
Stir slightly and bake until brown.

title: easy dessert
directions: Drain pineapple and place in a large bowl.
Add dry peach Jell-O.
Mix well.
Add Cool Whip and cottage cheese. Blend well.

title: yummy roast
directions: Mix all ingredients in large roaster.
Cook at 300° for 4 hours.
Cover and turn every 1/2 hour.
Best to cook the day before.
Cool and slice, then reheat at 300°.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add chocolate chips, nuts or whatever or leave plain to be frosted.
Drop by teaspoonful. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.
Frost if desired.

title: american enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Mix in chili.
In a separate pan, mix enchilada sauce, 1 tablespoon oil and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil and lower flame to simmer.
Take 1 tortilla and slide through sauce rapidly, covering it completely. Fill center with meat and sprinkle cheese to taste. Fold top down, bottom up; flip over and lay in pan.
Repeat until pan is filled.
Pour rest of enchilada sauce over top and sprinkle with rest of cheese.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 375°.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Wash grapes; drain.
Pick off and mash a little in order to get started cooking from their own juice.
(Remember, no water.) Let cook until they are done; pour into a bag and let drain.
When juice is ready, measure 5 cups juice and cook 20 minutes with the clock.
After juice is cooked, remove from fire at once.
Add 5 cups sugar; stir constantly until all is dissolved.
This will seem very thin for jelly after sugar is added and dissolved, but do not cook sugar in juice.
This makes a real grape flavor jelly. Cover with wax when cool.
In time, it will become like jelly.

title: my momma's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand and put in skillet or Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
When done, pour ketchup on top while hot.

title: diaper rash or chafing powder
directions: Stir together.
Pour into pint container with lid.
Place label on jar for safety.
Use as often as needed to affected areas.

title: cole slaw
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar, salad oil and salt together for 5 minutes.
Pour over cabbage, onion and pepper; mix.
Let set until cold, then refrigerate.
This will keep 2 weeks or longer.
Celery seed may be added if desired.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg on waxed paper.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup of flour mixture over raisins and nuts. Beat egg, butter and sugar in a bowl with mixture until fluffy. Combine tomato soup and lemon rind.
Add remaining flour mixture to butter mixture, beat until smooth.
Stir in raisins and nuts. Spoon into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour or until center springs back.
Let it cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Then wrap it in plastic wrap until it's served.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Cook hamburger and onion in skillet; drain.
In bowl, mix the corn meal, corn, eggs and enough milk to make a thin batter.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Beat eggs; add salt, broccoli, onion, cottage cheese and butter.
Mix and stir in cornbread mix.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Stir all ingredients thoroughly and store in a large container.
To make a cup of hot chocolate, use 1/3 cup mixture to 1 cup hot water.
Top with a small scoop of ice cream or a spoonful of Cool Whip.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together lemonade and condensed milk; fold in carton of Cool Whip.
Pour into baked pastry shell or graham cracker shell. Refrigerate.

title: baked potato dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add chives or chopped green onion tops to taste.
Store in refrigerator.

title: date nut balls
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt in bowl.
Mix in dates and nuts. Stir in eggs, blending well.
Spread out in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375°
for 15 minutes.
Remove to rack. Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Shape each square into a ball. Makes 25 balls.

title: mr. harry's pit cooked barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together in a large stainless steel or enamel pot and bring to boil.

title: company casserole
directions: Brown meat slightly.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Cook noodles and add butter to drained noodles.
Mix together cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, green pepper and scallions.
Butter a large casserole dish.
Layer half noodles, layer of all cheese mixture, then rest of noodles.
Top with meat layer, smoothing it over. Bake uncovered at 350° until bubbly and slightly brown on top for about an hour.
Freezes well.
Serves 8.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Chop the garlic fine.
Dice the tomatoes and mix with other ingredients.
Let stand for several hours in the refrigerator, overnight if possible.
Cook the spaghetti and leave at room temperature.
Toss the spaghetti and tomato mixture; enjoy.

title: killer cole slaw
directions: Combine all salad ingredients except noodles. Before serving toss with dressing. Add crushed noodles and toss again.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine all dry ingredients.
Whisk the milk, egg whites and applesauce together.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Stir only until moistened.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: beef roast
directions: Heat pressure cooker and add shortening.
Brown roast well on all sides; season with salt, pepper, bay leaf, onion, Worcestershire sauce and water.
Close top securely.
Place regulator at 15 pounds pressure and cook 40 to 45 minutes.
Turn stove off; let pressure drop off on its own before opening.
If desired, gravy can be made from liquid in cooker.
Serves 6.

title: mom's glorified sweet potatoes
directions: Slightly brown 8 (or more) slices pineapple in oleo.
Place pineapple slices on baking dish.
Top each with potato mixture. Bake about 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Top each with marshmallow and bake until marshmallows brown.

title: butterscotch log
directions: Melt
morsels
over
hot water.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk
and
vanilla.
Add
chopped pecans and mix well. Chill until firm.
Roll
into a log and place on waxed paper. Brush with beaten
egg white and press pecan halves into log. Keep refrigerated.

title: ham and cheese delights
directions: Remove rolls from pan and slice horizontally through entire pan of rolls; electric knife works well.
Saute onion in butter. Add poppy seed and mustard.
Spread top and bottom sections of rolls with butter mixture.
Place bottom half of rolls back in the pan.
Layer ham and cheese on bottom half.
Replace top.
Slice along joint lines to make individual rolls.
May be frozen at this point.
(Slicing is easier if rolls are partially frozen.) Wrap in foil and bake at 400° for 15 minutes or at 350° for 20 minutes if frozen.

title: miracle whip chocolate cake
directions: Measure sugar, flour, soda, and cocoa into sifter and sift into bowl. Add miracle whip salad dressing, vanilla and hot water. Mix together. Bake 40 minutes at 350 degrees in loaf or 30 minutes at 350 degrees in layers.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Melt butter and shortening in large skillet over low heat. Slice potatoes into the hot oil.
Cook over low heat until the edges of the potatoes are brown.
Turn potatoes and cook until brown.
Place cooked potatoes on a plate lined with a paper towel.
Sprinkle potatoes with salt and pepper.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix first four ingredients with fork or spoon (no beaters). Form in roll and roll in chopped pecans and parsley.
Chill well before serving.
Serve with crackers, Melba toast, etc.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; beat in eggs one at a time.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Grease and flour a large tube pan and pour in batter.
Bake slowly at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: curried shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter; add curry and celery salt.
Add rice, almonds and raisins.
Place in a baking dish and heat through at 350°.

title: timbale cases(like donuts)
directions: Combine egg, milk and shortening.
Add flour and salt; beat until smooth.
Let stand.
Heat timbale or rosette iron in deep, hot oil (375°).
Remove iron and drain.
Dip iron into batter, nearly to depth of iron.
If batter slips off, iron is too hot. Immerse batter-covered iron in hot oil and allow batter to come off iron.
Fry 30 seconds, until light and crisp.
Roll in confectioners sugar and put on a plate.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: In punch bowl or large bowl, layer Twinkies, cut in bite size. Mix pudding by directions, when thick layer on top of Twinkies. Then add pineapple (drained).
Then add cherries.
Then add Cool Whip on top.

title: beany kraut and franks
directions: Set aside
6 frankfurters;
cut remainder into 1/4-inch slices.
Combine
frankfurter slices and remaining ingredients in a large mixing
bowl;
mix well.
Spoon into a well greased shallow 2 quart
casserole,
bake
at
for
minutes. Arrange reserved frankfurters on top and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: steak marinade
directions: Puncture meat well with fork.
Sprinkle with tenderizer and garlic salt.
Pour soy sauce over meat and marinate overnight.

title: fried pie dough(by mildred "granny" carpenter)
directions: Sift all dry ingredients. Cut shortening into flour mixture. Beat together the egg and milk.
Add egg and milk mixture to flour mixture.
Roll out and cut to the size of a saucer.
Fill with fruit, fold over into a half moon and use pastry brush to brush edges with cream.
Seal edges.
Fry pies in skillet with Crisco until brown.
Then bake 15 minutes more in a 350° oven.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Add enough water to make one cup of water.
Bring to a boil.
Add jello and stir until dissolved. Stir in nuts and chill.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour peaches over the butter.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over the peaches. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dilly bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Heat cottage cheese and margarine to lukewarm.
Combine yeast and cottage cheese mixtures in bowl and add sugar, onion, dill seed, salt, soda and egg.
Add flour until stiff dough forms.
Cover; let rise until double.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Let rise in pan 30 to 40 minutes or until light.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.
Brush with butter.
Cool before slicing.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix together oil, cocoa and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, baking powder and salt.
Mix. Add flour.
Mix well. Chill for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs together.
To this add the flour, then add the vanilla, apples and pecans.
Mix well.
Bake in Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches and juice in loaf size baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk well.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 350° until top crust is brown (about 45 minutes).

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix altogether and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with crushed potato chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: university club cheese puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except baking powder and crackers, with electric mixer.
Then add baking powder and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.
Mound smoothly on crackers and bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: layer cake
directions: Mix together and pour in greased pan. Makes 3 layers or 1-9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° until done.

title: strawberry "ice cream"
directions: In a blender, add bananas, strawberries and milk, just enough to keep the blender from working hard and the frozen fruit is turning.
Add vanilla.
In a few seconds, the dessert will be mixed and have the consistency and flavor of ice cream.

title: dee's goop
directions: Brown ground beef, salt and pepper; drain well.
Mix beef, tomatoes and cheese.
Place in crock-pot or in a microwave dish. Melt.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Heat 1-inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Add cauliflowerets and broccoli.
Cover and heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cook 5 minutes.
Drain.
Rinse under running cold water; drain.
Rinse peas under running cold water to separate; drain.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk and pepper.
In buttered 1 1/2-quart greased casserole arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onion and sauce. Dot top with 1 tablespoon butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover; bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes more, until potatoes are done.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: garlic prawns
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl or secure zip-lock bag. Marinate at least 1 hour (best overnight). To cook, preheat oven to 500°. Spread prawns in a single layer on a jelly-roll pan or cookie sheet with a rim. Place on middle rack and bake for 5 minutes. Do not overcook. If necessary let it go one more minute, but no more.

title: carolina pulled barbecue pork
directions: Place onions in heavy Dutch oven cooker. Combine brown sugar, paprika, salt and pepper. Rub on roast. Place roast over onions. Combine vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, red pepper flakes, sugar, mustard, garlic salt and cayenne. Stir to mix well. Drizzle 1/3 of vinegar mixture over roast. Set remaining aside. Cover. Cook at 375° for 5 to 6 hours. Occasionally check on roast and pull meat away with a fork. Drizzle remaining vinegar mixture over roast during last 1/2 hour of cooking. Serve meat alone or on buns. Tastes really great with coleslaw.

title: orange-coconut salad
directions: Stir together first three ingredients (use Jell-O dry).
Drain next two ingredients and stir in.
Mix in remaining three ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: In a large skillet, fry hash browns according to package directions. Remove and set aside.

title: banana-lemon shake
directions: In blender, mix first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Add ice cream.
Blend again until smooth.
Makes 3 (8 ounce) servings.

title: strawberry champagne punch
directions: In blender, puree strawberries.
In punch bowl, combine pureed strawberries, lemon juice, sugar and wine; stir until sugar dissolves.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, butter and vanilla in electric blender container.
Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan.
Let stand about 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve warm or cool.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Put in slow cooker and add taco seasoning mix, Ro-Tel and cheese.
Serve warm with chips.

title: "frozen" salad
directions: Heat pineapple with juice to boiling; add the jello, stir until dissolved.
Put in refrigerator until partially set.
Add pimiento, nuts and celery to the softened cream cheese and mix well.
Add the jello mixture and stir; fold in the whipped cream.
Pour into a large mold (a Bundt cake pan is perfect) and set overnight in the refrigerator.
Dip mold into very hot water for a few seconds and unmold onto serving plate.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: In a large glass bowl, place butter and peanut butter. Microwave on High until butter melts (1 1/2 to 2 minutes).
Stir until blended.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until lumps of sugar disappear.
Microwave on High until softened, but not bubbly (1 to 1 1/2 minutes).
Pour into a buttered 9-inch square metal baking pan.
Cover; refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Makes 36 squares.

title: pastry for fried or cobbler pies
directions: Cut flour and shortening together.
Add 2/3 cup Pet milk with cold water to equal 1 cup and add beaten egg to milk, then add to flour mixture.
Work into a dough.
Roll thin and cut in circles. Spoon filling in center and fold over.
Crimp edges with fork dipped in water to seal.
Punch fork holes in top and fry in hot oil about 1/2 inch in electric skillet.
Drain on paper towel and sprinkle with powdered sugar (optional).

title: mrs. ramsey's zucchini tea cake
directions: Grease 2 loaf pans.
On wax paper sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon. In large bowl mix sugar, vanilla and oil; add 1 egg at a time.
Beat into mixture.
Stir in flour mixture with zucchini, nuts and raisins alternately until all mixed.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon, flour, nutmeg.
Spread over apples.
Place in pie shells and dot half oleo over this.
Cover with unbaked pie shell and dot remaining oleo.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french onion bread
directions: Soften dry yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Combine soup mix and 2 cups water; simmer covered 10 minutes.
Add sugar, salt, cheese and shortening; stir.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in 2 cups flour; beat well.
Stir in yeast.
Add enough of the remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface.
Cover; let rest 10 minutes.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in a lightly greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover.
Let double in warm place, 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Beat butter and peanut butter. Add graham crackers and powdered sugar. Press into an 8 x 8-inch pan. Melt chocolate chips and spread over peanut butter mixture.
Cool. Cut into squares.

title: first place chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and garlic; drain fat.
Add all remaining ingredients, except beans.
Simmer 3 hours.
Add beans. Simmer 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaves.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring butter, brown sugar and syrup to a boil in medium saucepan.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and baking soda.
Beat with wooden spoon.
Pour over popped corn and stir to coat.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: inexpensive party punch
directions: Mix all together.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Serves approximately 50.

title: burger and bean casserole
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Brown beef with onion and pepper; drain. Stir remaining ingredients together.
Add sugar, flour and browned beef.
Cover; bake 1 hour at 350° or until hot and bubbly.

title: zucchini oatmeal muffins
directions: Into a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, nuts, oatmeal, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
In a medium bowl, beat eggs slightly with fork. Stir in zucchini and oil.
Stir in egg mixture all at once into flour mixture just until flour is moistened. (Batter will be lumpy.) Fill muffin tins half full of batter and bake in a preheated 400° oven for 25 minutes.
Makes 25 medium muffins.
Freezes well.

title: crackling bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add the milk and stir in the cracklings.
Form into oblong cakes and place in a greased 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, arrange in layers the cracker crumb mixture.
Beat at high speed for 17 minutes the powdered sugar, eggs, margarine, bananas, pineapple and strawberries.
Spread Cool Whip over fruit.
Sprinkle top with chopped nuts and maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate for 8 hours.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.

title: susie's italian sausage soup
directions: Cut sausage into 1-inch pieces, brown and drain.
Combine celery, onion, parsley, garlic and oil in large kettle and saute until glossy.
Add tomatoes, puree, broth, oregano, bay leaves, thyme, sugar and rice.
Simmer for 1 hour, but longer is better, and eaten a day later is wonderful.

title: rice krispie morsels
directions: In a large saucepan, stir over medium heat the sugar and syrup until sugar is dissolved.
Add the peanut butter and mix well. Remove from heat. Stir in the Rice Krispies with wooden spoon. Spread mixture in buttered cookie sheet.
Spray hands or spoon with Pam and press mixture down firmly. Melt chips in top of double boiler.
Spread over Krispies mixture.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed.
Mix powder dressing with oil off the Italian dressing.
Put cooled spaghetti, tomatoes and green peppers in large bowl; mix.
Add Wish-Bone dressing and mix.
Stir together.
Let set 4 to 5 hours.
Before serving, mix again.

title: double pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. (Can also use iron skillet.)
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly in pan. Arrange drained pineapple slices and cherries on the sugar mixture.
Mix cake mix as directed on label with 1 1/3 cups water and 2 eggs.
(Do not substitute pineapple juice for water.)
Pour batter over fruit.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until cake tests done with a toothpick.
Let stand 5 minutes for topping to begin to set.
Then turn upside down onto large platter or cookie sheet.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: crunchy chicken and rice bake
directions: In large saucepan, combine soup with milk and heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in chicken, rice, beans, mushrooms, pimento, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake covered 40 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes more.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: mushroom medley
directions: Saute meat and onion.
Add tomatoes, catsup, seasonings, mushrooms and uncooked noodles (broken).
Cook on top of stove 1/2 hour.
Cover with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Recipe serves 6 plus.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well with salt and sugar.
Add part of milk and cream; add vanilla and rest of milk and cream.
Beat all together. Fill freezer not more than 3/4 full (it expands in freezer), then beat in freezer until it becomes foamy on top.
Add the ice and salt around the outside of the ice cream holder and turn until it becomes stiff.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Place sausage in casserole dish and pour rice-a-roni and cream of chicken soup and a little water and mix all together.
Grate cheese over top. Bake for about 25-30 minutes at 375°.

title: martha's pancakes(serves 4)
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together with pinch of salt. Beat eggs with milk.
Add oil.
Stir in flour mix.
Bake on hot griddle.

title: fruit jello mold
directions: Mix the ingredients together (except sour cream) and pour half into jello mold.
Place in freezer for 20 to 30 minutes until firm. Put sour cream on top of firm mixture and then pour remaining half of jello mixture on top of sour cream.
Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: claudia's onion pie
directions: Cook onions in butter until soft or tender.
Add to butter, eggs, milk and seasonings that will have been well beaten.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown in 450° oven.

title: frozen strawberry-yogurt pie
directions: Fold yogurt into whipped topping; blend well.
Fold in strawberries.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, 4 hours or overnight.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix all together.
Place in buttered casserole and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: italian bread soup
directions: Saute garlic and basil in olive oil in large saucepan until golden.
Add tomatoes; season to taste with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up tomatoes with a fork.
Soak bread in water to cover; squeeze dry.
Add bread, broth and half the cheese to tomato mixture; bring to a boil.
Simmer slowly 1 hour or until most of liquid is absorbed.
Add butter and remaining cheese.
Soup should thicken to consistency of porridge.

title: benny burgers
directions: Cook ground meat and onions together until lightly browned; drain.
Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper and water.
Add liquid smoke and simmer until liquid has cooked down.
Serve over light bread or hamburger buns spread with Miracle Whip salad dressing.

title: easy cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients well.
Pour cherry filling, pineapple and cake mix into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine and pour over top of mixture.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco ring
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium skillet, cook and stir beef over medium high heat until brown and pour off drippings.
Stir in seasoning mix, cheese and water; set aside.
Unroll crescent dough; separate into triangles.
Arrange triangles in circle on greased 14-inch pizza pan with wide ends overlapping in center and points toward outside.
There should be a 5-inch diameter opening in center.
Scoop meat mixture evenly onto widest end of each triangle.
Bring outside points of triangles down over filling and tuck under wide ends of dough at center.
Filling will not be completely covered.
Bake 20-25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut top off bell pepper and place in center of ring; fill with salsa. Mound lettuce, tomato, onion and olives on top of ring surrounding bell pepper.
Garnish with sour cream.

title: gram's chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with Stove Top stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: durango jim's slaw (crunchy)
directions: Use 1 part vinegar to 2 parts oil mixed with a little sugar or Fasweet.
Mix all ingredients together at last minute before serving.

title: e-z steak
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces and place in greased pan or casserole dish.
Combine soup and water and pour over meat. Sprinkle soup mix over top.
Cover.
Bake at 300° for 2 to 3 hours or use crock-pot.
Even tough meat turns out very tender.

title: rosies dip
directions: Brown meat and onion; add tomatoes and cook 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with Doritos. Keep dip in chafing dish.
May be spread on party bread squares and baked for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: shredded barbecued beef
directions: Combine beef, brown sugar, vinegar and water in 6-quart cast-iron or other heavy ovenproof pot.
Bake at 375° for 3 hours. Remove from oven; cool.
Remove all fat and any bones.
Shred beef; return to pot.
Add mixture of catsup, mustard, garlic and onion; stir to blend.
Reduce oven temperature to 300° and cook, covered, for up to 4 hours.
Stir every half hour, adding more water/catsup to keep well moistened.
Serve on buns with onion and cheese. Yields 12 to 14 servings.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Drain and add tuna, cream of mushroom soup, margarine, salt
and
pepper.
Simmer
on
stove until margarine is melted.

title: beet pickles
directions: Wash and drain beets.
Boil in water; remove skins.
Simmer together for 15 minutes the sugar, salt, spices, water and vinegar.
Cover the beets (packed in pint jars).
If not enough liquid to cover, add more vinegar.
Process pints and quarts for 30 minutes in boiling water bath or in pressure cooker for 5 minutes at 5 pounds pressure.

title: homemade meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand until well blended.
Add oats until firm consistency.
Place in a baking dish and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Loaf is done when browned and crispy on sides.

title: orange salad
directions: Spray Pyrex dish.
Put mixture of the cracker crumbs, melted margarine and sugar in bottom of dish.
Save a little for the top. Mix the orange juice, Eagle Brand milk, Cool Whip and oranges. Put on top of crumb mixture.

title: strawberry party cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Shape a small amount into a strawberry and then roll in the reserved jello which has been mixed with 4 tablespoons sugar and a little red food coloring.
Put 3 small leaves on with a leaf tube.
These freeze well.

title: crabmeat dip(hot)
directions: Mix ingredients well. Place in ovenproof bowl.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Prepare ahead.

title: feather rolls(heritage)
directions: In a mixer bowl combine 2 cups of flour and the yeast. Combine potatoes, oil, sugar, salt and 1 1/2 cups warm water (110°).
Add to dry ingredients; beat at low speed with electric mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping sides of bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in remaining flour.
Cover; refrigerate for at least 2 hours or up to 3 days.
Punch down; turn out on lightly floured surface.
Cover; let rest 10 minutes. With lightly floured hands, shape into 24 buns.
Place into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover; let rise until double (40 minutes).
Bake at 400° until done, 16 to 20 minutes.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Spread in bottom of a 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Pack firmly to make a crust.
Spread chocolate chips over crust. Follow with butterscotch chips, pecans then coconut.
Cover entire pan with eagle brand sweetened, condensed milk. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until coconut starts to brown. Enjoy!

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan.

Bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234° or a soft ball forms in cold water, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate bits until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: mexican chicken soup
directions: In a 3-quart heavy pot, bring two cans of broth to a boil. Add chicken tenders; reduce heat, cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes. Remove chicken; cut into bite-size pieces and return to pot. Add bouillon cube and tomatoes. Bring to a rolling boil; add rice and cook for 15 minutes. Add final can of chicken broth and heat through. Stir well and serve. Top each bowl of soup with shredded cheese and tortilla chips.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Arrange apples in greased square pan 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Mix remaining ingredients; sprinkle over apples.
Bake until topping is golden brown and apples are tender, about 30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.
Yields 6 servings.

title: green pineapple-cheese salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Heat together pineapple, sugar and lemon.
Mix pineapple and gelatin.
Refrigerate until set or next day.
Whip cream; add cheese, pecans and tint.
Add pineapple mixture; put in pretty glass bowl or on bed of lettuce leaves. Good for holidays.

title: irish fruitcake
directions: Combine raisins, currants, candied fruits and peels with 1/3 cup whiskey, molasses and fresh lemon peel. Mix well, cover and let stand overnight. Sift flour with salt, spices and baking powder. Cream butter and brown sugar together well. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Blend flour mixture into creamed mixture. Add fruits and coarsely chopped walnuts and mix well. Turn into a well-greased 9-inch bundt pan. Place a shallow pan of hot water on bottom of oven. Bake cake on lowest rack at 300° for 1 3/4 hours or until cake tests done. Let stand for 10 minutes, then invert onto wire rack and spoon remaining whiskey (about 4 Tbsp.) slowly over the cake so it soaks in. When cake is cold, wrap well in foil until serving time. To decorate after aging; mix a little powdered sugar with water to thin pouring consistency and tint lightly with green food coloring. Drizzle on cake. Sprinkle with green sugar crystals and arrange nutmeats on top.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spread in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes and cool.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and place in an 8-inch square casserole.
Pour on cream of mushroom soup.
Cover with frozen Tater Tots.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and cover with Velveeta cheese. Return to oven to melt cheese.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix thoroughly the first 4 ingredients.
Place in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° about 35 minutes.
When finished baking, add buttered bread cubes.
Return to oven and bake until cubes are lightly browned.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In saucepan over low heat melt chocolate with water, stirring 2 minutes, or until thick.
Remove from heat.
Gradually add syrup and salt.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring often.
Add vanilla.
Serve hot or cold on ice cream or cake.

title: the bon cherry cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well; make into balls.
Place a piece of cherry in center of each.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes, until browned.

title: carrot salad
directions: Use enough mayonnaise to hold salad together (about 2 heaping tablespoons).
You can add a banana if you use all your salad at one meal, otherwise it will turn dark.

title: chris' power shake
directions: In blender, combine ingredients and process until smooth. Drink heartily.

title: marinated crackers
directions: Mix
ingredients
together
and
pour
over 2 small (12 ounce) packages oyster crackers.
Put into airtight container. Stir occasionally for 24 hours.

title: chicken fry stew
directions: In a large frying pan, heat cooking oil.
Brown chicken on both sides, then add water to almost cover.
Simmer, covered, 45 minutes, checking on water; add as needed.
Add carrots and potatoes; cook until tender.
Thicken with mushroom soup.

title: apple bread
directions: Note:
This bread is a condensed sweetbread much like a banana bread.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix with stuffing.
Line dish with 1/2 mixture.
Mix other ingredients and spoon on top.
Add rest of stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oven dried tomato relish
directions: Core tomatoes and cut in half. Combine next four ingredients to make a pepper rub. Coat tomatoes with pepper rub and bake at 190° on a rack. Mix remaining ingredients and combine with roughly chopped tomatoes to make relish.

title: sauerkraut bake
directions: In large skillet fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towels, crumble and set aside.
Add onion to drippings in skillet.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring often until lightly brown and tender.
Drain on paper towels.
In large bowl combine tomatoes, sauerkraut, brown sugar, bacon and onion.
Turn the mixture into a 2-quart casserole. Cover and refrigerate at least 5 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: slop-in-a-dish
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
In large bowl, add rice, 1/2 the Velveeta cheese (diced), the can of Ro-Tel and the drained hamburger and onion.
Mix well while rice and hamburger are still hot to let cheese melt as much as possible.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Grate cucumber, onion and bell pepper. Mix all together. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Drain and serve.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and margarine until almost white.
Add eggs, beating after each egg.
Add vanilla and blend in flour.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours.

title: bread machine honey whole-wheat bread
directions: In bread machine pan, place all ingredients in order listed. Select basic bread setting (or whole-wheat setting if available). Choose crust color and 1 1/2-pound loaf size, if available. Bake according to bread machine directions. (Check dough after 5 minutes of mixing.) Add 1 to 2 tablespoons of water or flour if needed.

title: trail mix
directions: Julienne and dice dried fruits.
Chop nuts.
Add raisins, sunflower seeds and shredded coconut.
You may add other fruits and nuts to taste.
Mix all ingredients together and serve as snacks or treats.

title: broccoli madeline salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar for dressing. Wash and drain broccoli. Remove stalk and cut florets into bite-sized pieces. Combine broccoli, onion, bacon bits, cheese and raisins. Pour dressing over broccoli mixture and mix lightly. Chill well. Just before serving, top with sunflower seeds or pecans.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Put chicken (chopped in large chunks) into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add a layer of broken Doritos.
Put 1 stick of oleo in skillet and add chopped onion; cook until clear.
Add soups and Ro-Tel; add cheese.
After cheese has melted, pour over chicken and chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: no-bake date balls
directions: Put the cornflakes, dates and pecans into an electric blender or food processor and whirl just until well chopped or crush the cereal with your hands and chop the dates and nuts with a knife. In a mixing bowl, combine the cereal mixture with the honey, butter and lemon juice.
Knead until well mixed, then roll into 1 inch balls.
Sprinkle with sugar on a
sheet of wax paper, and roll the balls in the sugar.
Store in an airtight container.

title: ting a ling
directions: Melt chocolate pieces.
Remove from heat and pour over marshmallows and noodles.
Mix, then drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli spears for 5 minutes; drain well.
Return broccoli to pan and chop coarsely.
Add 1/2 stick butter and 1/2 pound Velveeta cheese (cut into small pieces).
Cover.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix and pour in a greased square pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: italian pizzelles
directions: *Do not use more than 1/2 cup butter and don't use oil.

title: bugs in the snow
directions: Mix all the ingredients well with a spoon; refrigerate. Serves 4 to 6.
Calories per serving:
This snack mixture is delicious alone or served on graham.

title: cauliflower-ham au gratin
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Arrange cauliflower in 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with ham.
Beat soup with milk until smooth.
Pour over ham.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly and sprinkle over soup mixture.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Spread in a pie shell. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then lower oven to 325°, baking for another 30 minutes.

title: salmon and cheese loaf
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid.
Flake salmon and crush bones. In a bowl, beat egg.
Add salmon, reserved liquid, grated cheese, bread crumbs, onion, melted butter, salt, pepper and basil.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into an uncooked 9-inch pie shell.
Cover with top pastry.
Cook for 55 minutes or until crust is brown at 350°.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except sour cream and 1/2 the jello. Spoon 1/2 mixture into serving dish.
Spread sour cream on top. Add remaining 1/2 of jello mixture.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: the next best thing to robert redford
directions: Mix chocolate pudding and set aside.
Mix vanilla pudding and set aside.
Cream together flour, margarine and chopped pecans. Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.
Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread on crust and let stand in refrigerator 10 minutes. Mix puddings and milk together and spread over cream cheese.
Mix vanilla with rest of whipped cream; put on top.
Grate Hershey Bar over top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: braised celery bites(serve with poultry)
directions: About 20 minutes before serving in a 10-inch skillet over high heat in boiling water, heat celery and next 3 ingredients to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium; cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes until celery is tender-crisp.
Drain celery.
Return to skillet. Stir in butter until melted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: monkey bread(this is a fun bread to make with your children!)
directions: In a large bowl or mixer, stir together 1 1/2 cups flour, yeast, sugar and salt; set aside.
Heat milk and 1/3 cup butter until very warm and pour over flour and yeast mixture.
Add egg and beat 3 minutes at medium speed, occasionally scraping bowl. Add 1 cup of flour and beat 3 minutes longer.
Stir in remaining 2 1/2 cups flour and mix with a wooden spoon until thoroughly blended.

title: fancy franks
directions: Mix ingredients in crock-pot.
Heat until hot.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
In medium bowl, combine flour, soda and salt.

title: apple dessert
directions: Place sliced apples in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon to taste.
Mix first 5 ingredients together and place on top of apples.
Bake at 350° until browned, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: beat-n-eat icing
directions: Mix together.
Add 1/4 cup boiling water.
Beat until peaks form.

title: stuffed flounder
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter, add mushrooms and parsley and simmer 5 minutes.
Add a pinch of cayenne pepper and black pepper.
Stir in scallops and crab sticks.
Simmer 7 minutes. Add lemon (wine - optional at this point).
Place 3 flounder fillets on a baking tray and lay stuffing over each, top with remaining fillets.
Bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 8 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon together.
Cream sugar and Wesson oil in separate bowls, then add eggs.
Add flour and pecans.
Add the grated carrots last.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: shrimp ouchey
directions: Saute garlic and shallots in 1/2 stick butter until golden. Add cleaned and deveined shrimp with 1/2 stick butter.
Cook until shrimp are pink (about 5 minutes).
Add stock and cook over medium heat for 2 minutes.
Remove shrimp.
Bring remaining liquid to a boil and reduce by one-half.
Add cream.
Cook until thick.
Add shrimp.
Serve over toasted French bread slices.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Simmer fresh or frozen oysters in their own liquid until the edges begin to curl.
Drain and chop coarsely, saving the liquid. If using canned oysters, drain, reserve juice and chop.

title: nutty nanna pops
directions: Blend all ingredients in a medium-size bowl.
Spoon mixture into 6 (3 ounce) wax paper or plastic cups.
Freeze 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until mixture is partially frozen.
Insert a wooden stick into the center of each cup and freeze for several hours until firm.
Peel off cups before serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together; put in baking dish.
Lay 2 slices bacon on top.
Pour one 8 ounce tomato sauce on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pork chops and potato bake
directions: Brown pork chops in butter or margarine.
Remove from pan when done.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Make light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add flour and beat in lemon extract and 7-Up.
Bake in well-greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Combine with all other ingredients, except biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Top with biscuits and bake 15 to 20 more minutes.

title: hot cocoa mix(club member: john waters)
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well. Store in airtight container.

title: hot milk unwinder
directions: Place all ingredients in saucepan; heat to just below boiling.

title: fruit jello
directions: Add enough water to juice to make 3/4 cup.
Add pineapple, sour cream and nuts.
Place in bowl or mold and chill.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in graham cracker shells and refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pineapple snow
directions: Put evaporated milk in freezer overnight or for several hours. Make jello, using pineapple juice with water equal to 2 cups. Chill until firm.
Make whipped cream using evaporated milk, lemon juice, drained pineapple and sugar.
When jello is firm, fold in cream mixture.
Crush vanilla wafers and cover bottom of large cake pan.
Pour mixture over crumbs.
Garnish with a few crumbs.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together.
Add cold water until texture is desired.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Place pecans in prepared pastry shell.
Combine chocolate and butter in a pan.
Cook over low heat, stirring until smooth. Remove from heat and add corn syrup and remaining ingredients. Pour over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli according to package directions (don't overcook).
Drain.
Mix soup, cheese, mayo and onion flakes.
Blend in eggs.
Toss lightly with broccoli.
Turn lightly into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix bread crumbs with melted Parkay; sprinkle over all.
Bake 40 minutes uncovered or until bubbly.

title: sausage and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as box directions.
After ready, add green onions and soup.
Cook broccoli spears as directions until tender.
Drain off water.
Add to rest of the ingredients the sausage.
Pour into large, deep covered casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix oleo, cream cheese and flour together.
Chill 1 hour. Roll into 24 balls.
Press into tart pans.

title: tater nugget hot dish
directions: Heat oven to 375°. In large saucepan, brown ground beef, onions and celery until beef is thoroughly cooked. Drain well.

title: lime marshmallow jello
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk.
Stir in Jell-O.
Beat in cream cheese until smooth.
Add pineapple and whipping cream.
Chill and serve.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Microwave butter in 9-inch glass dish on Medium-high for 2 minutes or until melted.
Stir in brown sugar.
Arrange pineapple slices in dish.
Place cherry in center of each slice.
Prepare cake mix using package directions.
Pour over pineapple slices. Microwave on Medium for 7 minutes.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes or until cake tests done.
Let stand for 1 minute.
Invert onto serving plate.
Serve warm or cool.
Serves 6.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Put popped corn in brown paper bag.
Mix brown sugar, margarine, light syrup and salt.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes. Stir after each minute until it boils, then boil 2 minutes more. Add baking soda; stir.
Pour over corn in bag.
Close and shake. Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake again; microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake bag.
Pour into pan to cool.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon slowly and pour off some of the fat.
Brown chopped onion and beef in fat.
Add seasonings.
Add tomatoes and well washed rice.
This will be a thick mixture at the end of cooking period.
If desired thinner, add a cup of water.
When ready to serve, lightly stir to bring up color of tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or more.

title: lemonade and vodka punch
directions: Mix sherbet and ice cubes.
Add remaining ingredients, putting vodka in last.
Stir and serve.

title: coffee punch
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Blend well.
Place ice cream in punch bowl and pour in coffee mixture.
Top with whipped cream and nutmeg, if desired.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until tender.
Put all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat well; do not clean beaters as they collect potato strings.
Pour into the unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until set and lightly browned.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine nuts, dates, water and baking soda in a bowl and let cool.
In a separate bowl, beat together the oil, egg and sugar. Add this mixture to the original one of nuts and dates.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, cocoa and vanilla and beat all together well.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti and meat balls
directions: Cook meatballs well done.
Add spaghetti, onion and tomatoes. Cook until tender.
Add spices and sauce (if used) to suit individual taste.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and salt in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil until the soft ball stage is reached, then remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, butter and peanut butter.
Beat off some of the gloss.
Put in pan or a large plate to cool.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all together, except crumbs.
Using a buttered casserole, alternate layers of mixture and crumbs, leaving a few crumbs for the top.
Bake 20 minutes at 250°, covered,
then at 20 minutes at 350°, covered.
Remove cover and brown slightly.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Cream butter and cheese together. Add flour, salt and cayenne pepper and mix well. Add Krispies and mix well. Mixture will be stiff. Pinch a small piece of mixture, place on cookie sheet, and flatten with fingers as thin as possible. This will be the size and thickness of the baked cracker. Bake at 325° for 11-13 minutes. Makes 8-9 dozen.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Combine cheese and crab in a small bowl. Divide crab mixture among the upside down mushroom caps, stuffing the mushrooms. Brush 1 phyllo sheet with the butter/olive oil mixture. Cover with another sheet and brush with more melted butter. Make 7 layers. Cut phyllo sheets into 4 squares. Place mushroom, cheese side up, in the center of each square. Season with salt and pepper. Repeat 5 more times to make 20 squares. Lift sides of pastry over mushrooms to resemble small bundles and form a "neck, " pinching edges together to seal. Place on a greased baking sheet and brush with beaten egg. Bake for about 15 minutes until pastry is crisp and golden. Serve hot.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a casserole dish.
Stir remaining ingredients together and pour over potatoes.
Put in oven and bake at 350° until real bubbly.

title: barbecue sauce for ribs(per slab)
directions: Mix ketchup, brown sugar, mustard and honey well.
Coat meat before cooking.
When meat has 30 minutes more to cook, brush with mixture of pineapple juice, brown sugar and 1/2 pint honey.

title: jumbo shells(spinach and ricotta filling)
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Squeeze excess moisture out. In skillet, cook onion in butter till just tender.
Add spinach. In bowl, mix egg, cheeses, nutmeg and spinach mixture.
Stuff shells.
Pour spaghetti sauce over shells and heat in 375 degree oven for 20 minutes.

title: sweet sandwich spread
directions: In blender, grind lemon, peel and all.
Add raisins.
Mix with sugar and egg.
Cook in double boiler until it begins to thicken, stirring often.

title: shrimp pizzas
directions: Mix cheese, mayonnaise, shrimp, curry powder and onions. Toast muffins.
Spread shrimp mixture on muffin halves and broil until bubbly.
Can be made in advance and frozen before boiling. Cut into fours.
Yields 48 pieces.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except 1 cup nuts.
Shape into ball.
Roll cheese ball in 1 cup of the nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, oil, milk, in a large mixing bowl. Add chopped nuts and oats. Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 350 degrees until slightly brown around edges.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Warm mixture in microwave or in saucepan over low heat.
Serve with apple slices.

title: bobotee
directions: Fry onions in the margarine until soft.
Soak bread in milk and squeeze.
Soak raisins in the extra milk.
Soften and chop the dried apricots.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven in a meat loaf or bread pan for at least 1 hour.

title: spareribs and sauerkraut
directions: Cook spareribs in a pot until tender.
(Save some of the broth to cook with rice.)
Add sauerkraut to broth and bring to a boil. Drain and pour into baking dish.
Place spareribs on top and bake in oven at 450° until brown. Turn the spareribs and brown on both sides.

title: creamed onions
directions: Make cream sauce.
Add drained onions, cooked peas and pimientos.

title: weight loss soup
directions: Mix all ingredients except cabbage in large pot; cook about 15 minutes, then add cabbage and cook until cabbage is tender.
If you eat this twice a day, there can be weight loss of 5 to 8 pounds per week.
The more soup you eat, the more weight you will lose.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Put dough into 15 x 10-inch pan, sealing the perforations. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until done.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Spread over cooled crust.
Top with raw vegetables such as broccoli, green onions, tomatoes, cucumbers, carrots, etc.

title: cherry's golden cherry crunch cake
directions: Mix together flour and melted oleo.
Add nuts.
Press this mixture into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350° (slightly brown).
Do not overcook.
Cool.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix pumpkin, sugar, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
With a fork, lightly beat eggs into pumpkin mixture.
Add milks; mix well.
Place a pastry-lined 9-inch pie plate on oven rack.
Pour in pumpkin mix.
Bake in a 375° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: apricot jello
directions: Dissolve the jello with the hot water; let cool.
Add the apricots, pineapple and marshmallows.
Let set.

title: cheese bread
directions: Unroll crescent rolls to fill bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Seal together by pushing together.
Seal seams!
Beat cream cheese, egg yolk, vanilla, sugar, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Spread over rolls.
Spread crushed pineapple over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining rolls.
Seal seams.
Brush with egg whites.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pickled okra
directions: Boil the first five ingredients and pour over okra, pepper, garlic and dill which have been placed in jars.
Seal.

title: new england fish chowder
directions: In saucepan combine potato, onion and fish.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Add salt and pepper; simmer until vegetables are tender and fish flakes, about 30 minutes.
Add dry milk and stir well.
Remove from heat and break fish into bite-size pieces. Add margarine and stir until it melts.
Yield:
1 serving.

title: mom's biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.	Cut in Crisco. Add milk. Knead with floured hands a few times. Cut out. Place on baking sheet, just touching. Bake at 450° for 14 minutes.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Put rice in bottom of casserole.
Lay pieces of chicken on top of rice.
Pour mixed soups over chicken.
Cook at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook green peppers and celery in margarine until soft (about 5 minutes). Add tomato sauce, water, salt, onion and shrimp.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: spinach-artichoke casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Saute onions in butter.
Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and also sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake salmon with a fork.
Combine with other ingredients in a bowl; mix well.
Pour mixture into a greased pan or casserole dish.
Do not cover.
Position pan in center of barbecue grate and cook 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: oreo freakout dessert
directions: Place 1/2 c. cookie crumbs aside.
Combine remaining crumbs with melted butter and press into 9X13 pan.
Soften ice cream until it can be easily spread over crumbs.
Freeze at least 30 minutes.
Spread peanuts over ice cream.
Heat fudge in microwave 1-2 minutes; drizzle over ice cream.
Freeze.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with cookie crumbs.
Keep frozen.

title: pork and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Partially freeze pork, trim excess fat from pork.
Slice across grain into 2 x 1/4-inch strips and set aside.
Wipe mushrooms with damp paper towel; remove stems and reserve for another use.
Slice caps and set aside.
Wash broccoli and remove flowerets, reserve stalks for another use.
Cut flowerets into small pieces; set aside.
Coat a wok or skillet with cooking spray; add oil and place over high heat until hot.
Add pork; stir-fry 4 minutes or until lightly browned.
Add mushroom caps, carrots and soy sauce.
Cover and reduce heat to low and cook 8 minutes.
Add broccoli; cover and cook 3 minutes or until broccoli is crisp-tender.

title: 15-minute chicken gumbo
directions: Coat a large skillet with nonstick cooking spray. Add vegetables and saut over high heat, stirring frequently for 2 minutes. Stir in flour and cook 1 minute more. Stir in tomatoes, chicken and Creole seasoning. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently until hot, about 6 minutes. Yields about 1 1/2 cups per serving.

title: chicken-almond sandwiches
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Set aside.
Cut bread rounds in half.
Fill each half full with lettuce and alfalfa sprouts. Spoon in chicken mixture.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Yield: 8 sandwiches.

title: chili pepper casserole
directions: Combine last 5 ingredients.
Layer in casserole, starting with cream mixture, tortillas, ending with cream mixture and more grated cheese on top.
Let set overnight or make in morning to be baked that evening.
Bake 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and mix 3 to 4 minutes.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with milk.
Mix in flavorings.
Pour into a greased and floured 10 tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake test done.
Cool about 10 minutes and add glaze if desired.

title: doctor bird cake
directions: Put dry ingredients in bowl.
Add oil.
Add pineapple, bananas, vanilla and eggs.
Stir to blend, but do not beat.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour 15 minutes. Cool in pan on rack before turning out of pan.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheeses and dip set until room temperature.
Mix all ingredients and 1/2 of nuts.
Form into a large ball and cover with remaining nuts.

title: chicken paprikash with dumplings
directions: Sprinkle chicken parts on all sides with salt and 2 teaspoons paprika.
Melt margarine in large skillet; add chicken.
Saute until golden.
Turn pieces; add onion.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon paprika.
Simmer, covered, 20 minutes.
Add 2 cups broth; cook slowly, covered, until tender.
Remove chicken; keep warm.
Blend sour cream, 1/2 cup water and flour until smooth.
Gradually add to broth in skillet.
Cook and stir over low heat until thickened. Return chicken to sauce.
Keep on low heat, uncovered, until serving time.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Reserve bread crumbs, nuts and oleo for top. Mix all other ingredients and pour into a large greased shallow casserole. Add bread crumbs and nuts. Dot with oleo. Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes. Serves 8.

title: tomato jam
directions: Mix tomatoes and sugar.
Boil 15 minutes; stir often.
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O.
Stir well.
Put in containers.
Put in refrigerator for one day.
Then store in freezer.
Makes 2 pints.

title: baked pineapple bread pudding
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add pineapple. Stir in bread.
Bake in a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
(If you use Pyrex, reduce heat to 325°.)

title: bengetti casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage (I use hot sausage) and onion.
Drain grease.
Add tomato and cream of mushroom soup.
Cook egg noodles. Drain and add to meat.
Put in large casserole (or 2 small ones) and cover with Velveeta cheese.
Bake in oven at 325° until cheese melts, about 10 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Melt butter, add sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and mix well. Spread into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: ohio buckeyes
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Roll into little balls; refrigerate.
Melt the chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls into chocolate coating; let stand on wax paper until coating hardens.
Refrigerate.
Serves 40 to 50.

title: chicken tetrazzinigroves, texas
directions: Cook fryer until tender and debone.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Then make white sauce.

title: honey chicken
directions: Combine honey, mustard, melted butter and curry.
Remove skin from chicken.
Dip each piece of chicken in sauce and place in a large greased roasting pan.
Pour remaining sauce over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix and cool the nuts, dates, raisins, hot water and baking soda.
Mix and add the sugar, flour, cocoa, cinnamon, mace, salt, oil and egg.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Cut fruit in small pieces.
Cover bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with lemon.
In a bowl, mix sugar, butter and cinnamon. Place on top of fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour lettuce
directions: Break lettuce in small pieces; slice onions thin. Break apart. Cube bacon and brown.
Add vinegar, sugar and water mixture. Just before serving, pour over lettuce.
Vinegar mixture may be adjusted to taste.

title: nova scotia mousse
directions: Sprinkle 1 envelope unflavored gelatin into 1/4 cup cold water.
Dissolve in 1/2 cup hot light cream.
Cool.
Mash together cream cheese, sour cream, Worcestershire sauce, hot pepper sauce and chopped chives.
Stir into gelatin mixture.
Add lemon juice, parsley, horseradish, salmon and black olives.
Fold in caviar. Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart mold.

title: beef and peppers in hot mustard sauce
directions: Cut steak across grain on diagonal into thin strips.
In a medium bowl mix together egg white, cornstarch, lemon juice and 2 tablespoons soy sauce.
Add beef slices and toss to coat.

title: blueberries, peach cobbler(diabetic)
directions: Mix berries, sugar and butter or oleo in pot.
Add flour in cup of water and mix until smooth.
