Add to berries mixture.
Let cook for 1/2 hour.
Pour 1/2 into pie shell.
Brown one pie shell. Put on top of mixture and the rest of filling.
Cover with third pie shell.
Punch a couple of holes in top shell.
Add three pats of butter or oleo.
Sprinkle 1 package of Equal over the top. Bake until crust is brown at about 350°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Crumble bread.
Mix cheese and bread, and spread in bottom of greased 7 1/2 x 12-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs and milk together and stir in seasonings.
Pour this over bread and cheese mixture.
Lay bacon on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Remove from oven just after guests sit down, otherwise it may tend to fall.

title: sole stuffed with crab meat
directions: Remove cartilage from crabmeat.
In medium skillet, melt butter and saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Place in a bowl.
Add crabmeat, bread crumbs, egg, parsley, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce and mix thoroughly.
Lay fillets flat and place approximately 1/3 cup of filling on each piece.
Roll up and place seam-side down in a shallow 2-quart buttered baking pan. Pour lemon juice over fish.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake in 350°
oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate praline layer cake
directions: Preheat

oven to 325°. Grease 2 (8 or 9-inch) round cake pans. Combine butter, whipping cream and brown sugar in a small saucepan. Cook over low heat just until butter is melted, stirring occasionally. Pour evenly into prepared pans; sprinkle evenly with chopped pecans. Combine cake mix, water, oil and eggs in a large bowl; beat at low speed until moistened and then beat at high speed for 2 minutes. Carefully spoon batter over praline mixture in pans. Bake 35 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched with finger. Cool layers in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes. Loosen edges and remove to racks to cool completely.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and potato chips. Pour into baking pan and top with cheese and chips.
Bake at 450 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: manaroni
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper.
Meanwhile, cook egg noodles as directed.
Drain noodles.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, combine noodles, ground beef and soups.
Mix well.
Top with Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon and milk in 2-quart pan. Bring to boil, stirring constantly. Continue at low boil to 236°.
Remove from heat. Add nutmeats and vanilla. Stir and pour onto wax paper; separate. Serve warm or cold. Store in covered container in refrigerator or freezer. Makes 1 1/4 pounds.

title: spring cauliflower scallop
directions: Separate cauliflower into flowers.
Place in shallow baking dish, 10 x 6 x 2-inches.
Blend soup, milk and cheese.
Pour over cauliflower. Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bubbling.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: wild rice with turkey
directions: Combine rice mix, soup and broth in a 2-quart microproof casserole.
Cover with casserole lid.
Cook on High for 10 minutes.
Stir in turkey, mushrooms and celery seed.
Cover and cook on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until rice is cooked.
Remove from oven and let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 servings.
Cooking time:
12 to 13 minutes.

title: sugar-free banana pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add hot water and cook over medium heat until mixture starts to thicken.
Add beaten egg yolks and cook approximately 2 minutes.
Add margarine, vanilla and Equal.
Pour over layered vanilla wafers and bananas.
Top with beaten egg whites if desired, then bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: dill pickle dip
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat with mixer until well mixed.
If too thick, add a little more dill pickle juice.

title: chicken dumplins
directions: Work flour and Crisco together with fork.
Add 1/4 cup water. Work together with a fork.

title: holiday jello mold
directions: Mix Jell-O according to package directions and then add pecans, pineapple and strawberries to the mixture.
Pour half of the mixture into a mold and refrigerate until solid.
After Jell-O has jelled, then spoon the sour cream over the solid Jell-O.
Next add remainder of the Jell-O mixture on top of sour cream; refrigerate until firm.

title: kentucky fruit pie
directions: Fold in Cool Whip with all other ingredients.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugars gradually.
Blend well.
Add vanilla, then eggs; beat well.
Add dry ingredients. Fold in oatmeal, nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: caramel fried apples
directions: Pare apples; cut in good sized pieces.
Let the butter become hot; add apples, sugar and water.
Cook (without stirring) until apples are soft and sugar and butter become golden brown on the bottom of the pan.
Serve with meat.
Serves six.

title: creamy whipped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into quarters.
Salt to taste and boil for 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.
Combine potatoes, cream cheese, garlic salt, pepper and 4 tablespoons margarine. Blend well.
Gradually add heavy cream, mixing well after each addition.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise and cream cheese together and add remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Peel and dice eggplant.
Cook in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain well and set aside.
Brown onion in 1 tablespoon butter.
Add to eggplant.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter and mix in cracker crumbs.

title: saucepan scotchies
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Remove pan from heat and add sugar and blend.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Stir in vanilla, flour and baking powder.
Add nuts and stir lightly. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: quick orange salad
directions: Mix dry jello with cottage cheese.
Add other ingredients. Keep in fridge.
Blend well.

title: zippy macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Set aside.
Dice onion up and cook with ground beef for 10 minutes.
Add macaroni and tomatoes, then bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: adaline hanover's salmon cutlets
directions: Saute the green onions in the butter.
Add the flour; cook and stir, but don't let get brown.
Add the milk; stir until thick. Let cool.
Add the salmon, crushed crackers and the beaten eggs. Taste for salt.
Fry in patties.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soften stuffing mix in eggs and catsup.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers and remove seeds; put in boiling water for 5 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Mix ingredients.
Fill peppers. Put in baking dish with a small amount of water.
Cover top of peppers with tomato soup or catsup.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: 3 layer chocolate pie
directions: Mix and press in 9 x 12 inch pan the margarine, pecans and flour.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until brown.
Cool.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and pour in casserole dish.
Add topping before baking at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli in water with no salt.
Bring to boil; drain. Melt Cheez Whiz in the cream of chicken soup, then mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs, together.
Put into buttered casserole.
Put buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: luscious banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, layer wafers, bananas and pudding mix and layer again.
Top with crumbs of wafers.
You can keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: oreo stuff
directions: Crumble Oreos into softened ice cream.
Mix well.
Place in a 13-inch plastic container.
Spoon Cool Whip on top.
Chill in freezer for 2 hours.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except for 1/4 cup barbecue sauce or ketchup. Shape meat into 2 oval loaves. Top with remaining barbecue sauce or ketchup. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until center is no longer pink.

title: yum-yum cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Add pineapple.
Mix flour and baking powder, then add to pineapple mixture.
Pour into greased pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (may take longer; bake until top is brown).

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place single layer of meatballs on ungreased baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Place meatballs in 2-quart dish.
Combine sauce ingredients (next 9 ingredients) and pour over meatballs. Bake 1 hour longer.

title: summer fried tomatoes
directions: Dip tomato slices in flour.
Cook in margarine over low heat until lightly browned on both sides; remove to heated plate.
Stir soup and milk into skillet; heat, stirring occasionally.
Pour sauce over tomatoes.

title: royalty snack
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in an airtight container until ready to serve.
Serve in foil cups.
This is very good around holiday time.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding pecans last.
Pour into unbaked
9-inch
pastry
shell.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 36 minutes longer. Filling should appear
less
set in center than outer edge.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Cook carrots until firm and tender.
Drain; add chopped onions and green pepper.
Mix other ingredients together.
Toss with vegetables.
Chill.

title: eggless chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a 9 x 13 pan. Make 3 wells. Pour vanilla in one. Pour oil in one. Pour vinegar in one. Pour water over top. Mix but don't beat. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Very moist. Serve with or without frosting.

title: lemon basil carrots
directions: Cook carrots and drain.
Melt butter.
Add dry ingredients and toss with carrots.
Serves 6.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: In a small bowl, combine all of the ingredients; stir the dressing well.
Spoon over coleslaw made with shredded cabbage and carrots.
Chopped onions and green pepper may be added.

title: green salad with dilled shrimp
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, lemon juice, dill, salt, pepper, mustard and garlic and mix well.
Pour this mixture over the shrimp and set in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Remove from refrigerator and add lettuce and cucumber, toss well.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef and onion over medium heat; drain fat.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Bring to a boil; simmer 5 minutes.
Slice zucchini crosswise into 1/4-inch slices. In a small bowl, combine cottage cheese and egg.
In a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan, place half of the zucchini and sprinkle with half of the flour.
Top with cottage cheese mixture and half of the meat mixture.
Repeat with zucchini and flour.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and remaining meat.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix.
Pour half of batter in pan and bake for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on cake.
Melt caramels, butter and milk.
Pour over cake and then pour rest of batter on top and bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: burnt almond fudge ice cream
directions: Toast almonds in 300° oven for 14 mins., stirring occasionally.
Blend in pan, sugar and cocoa, then add beaten eggs, canned milk and 4 cups of half and half.
Stir and heat until almost boiling.
Cool, then add remaining half and half, whipping cream and extract.
Add nuts just before freezing.
Pour into a 6 qt. ice cream freezer and freeze.
Very good and creamy.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix well until moist and
smooth.
Pat	in
pan or roll into balls.
Cook at 350° until brown.

title: mountain dew cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order. Pour batter in 3 layer pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: biscotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 4 ingredients in a large bowl with wooden spoon.
Combine baking powder with flour and add to egg mixture, 1/2 cup at a time.
Add nuts and mix.
Divide dough into 6 portions and dust with a little flour to prevent stickiness.
Form each into a loaf shape on an ungreased cookie sheet (3 loaves on 1 cookie sheet).
Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Remove from oven.
Immediately cut each loaf on a slant. Return to oven on side and bake until golden.

title: quarkstollen
directions: Soak raisins in rum in jar overnight.
Mix together other ingredients.
Knead with mixer.
Turn out and work by kneading on surface.
Add the raisins and keep kneading until smooth dough. Shape into loaf.
Put on baking sheet lined with greaseproof paper.
Bake at 160° to 180° C. for 50 to 60 minutes.
Brush with 100 g. melted butter and 50 g. icing sugar when stollen is removed from oven.

title: apple orchard punch
directions: Combine orange, apple, and cranberry juice in a large punch bowl. Stir to dissolve. At serving time, add ginger ale. Float apple slices on top.

title: apache fry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water (more if needed).
Knead for 5 minutes on a floured surface.
Divide into 16 balls.
Roll each ball out on floured surface to about 6 to 8-inch diameter.
Poke a hole in the middle and fry, one at a time, in 1/2-inch hot grease. Splatter hot grease on the top so it will puff up some.
Turn over.
Cook until both sides are golden brown.
Top with honey, powdered sugar or like a tostada with meat, beans, lettuce, tomato and onion.

title: rum balls
directions: Place all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix with hands until well blended.
Shape into small balls, marble size.
Roll in coconut, powdered sugar or cocoa.
Freezes well.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Cook to a boil the first four ingredients.
Boil 3 minutes. Take off heat.
Add vanilla and peanuts.
Beat until cools and thickens.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: eggnog pie
directions: Mix the pudding mix, nutmeg and eggnog in a saucepan and cook over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Chill.
Beat the rum with whipped cream until smooth and fold into the pudding mixture; pour into the pie shell.
Garnish with nutmeg and chill for 4 hours.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Dredge cheese in flour, then sprinkle cheese and ham evenly into pie crust.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over cheese and ham mixture.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Make sure crust does not burn.
Cool slightly and serve.

title: pizza chicken or turkey
directions: Flatten the 6 fillets with a kitchen mallet.
Dip in beaten egg, then in cracker meal.
Brown lightly in oil.
Drain well and place in a single layer in baking dish.
Top each fillet with a slice of Mozzarella of a size approximately the same.
Cover all with pizza sauce to which 1/2 teaspoon salt has been added.
Cover baking dish closely with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovering for the last 5 minutes, if desired.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese.
Freezes well.
Serves 6.
(Can be prepared ahead of time, refrigerated and cooked just before serving.)

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking soda, sugar and cinnamon.
Stir in pecans.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into two greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for one hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes, remove and let cool on wire racks.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. In a large plastic bag (or bowl), mix all ingredients. Close bag and shake until potatoes are evenly coated. Spread in shallow pan. Bake for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and brown.

title: chicken-broccoli skillet
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Season chicken strips.
Cook chicken and chopped onion quickly in hot margarine until chicken is done. Stir in thawed broccoli, lemon juice, salt, thyme and pepper. Cook covered 6 minutes.
Add tomato wedges.
Cover 3 to 4 more minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll biscuits out and fill with the chopped apples.
Pinch up and fold over.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: biscuits (using mix)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Stir most of water together with mix. Add more water as needed to make a dough that is soft but not too sticky to knead. Knead dough 15 minutes on lightly floured surface. Pat or roll dough into square about 7 x 7-inch. Cut into 16 pieces and place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake about 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Mix cherries, sugar and water.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple and Coca-Cola. Refrigerate.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix together in blender the strawberries, lemonade and pineapple.
Mix thoroughly; add ginger ale.
Stir to mix.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in bottom of pan.
Pour peaches in and smooth them out.
Make a batter with flour, sugar and milk.
Smooth out batter.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° until brown.
You may double or triple this recipe for more people.

title: clam chowder
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook on medium heat for 1 hour.

title: white salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 cup pineapple juice and cream cheese and stir until evenly blended.
Add pineapple, celery and nuts.
Gently fold in whipped cream and pimentos.
Pour in dish or mold to chill overnight.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: 60 minute yeast rolls
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast in large mixing bowl.
In saucepan, heat milk, water and margarine until very warm (120° to 130°).
Margarine doesn't have to melt.
Add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes with mixer.
Stir in 1/2 cup flour and beat on high 2 minutes.
Stir in additional flour to make soft dough.
Turn onto board and knead 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; let rise 15 minutes.
Shape into rolls.
Cover and let rise 15 minutes.
Bake in 425° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli buds.
Peel and chop onion.
Mix broccoli, shredded cheese, chopped onion and crumbled bacon in large mixing bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar in small bowl and add to the broccoli mixture.
Let stand about 4 hours before serving, stirring occasionally.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Butter and flour a 3 x 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda into bowl and set aside.
Put egg, shortening, salt, orange rind, sugar and juice into blender.
Cover and process until blended.
Add nuts and cranberries and process only until chopped.
Empty into flour mixture and mix only until blended.
Spoon into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for about 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Yield: 1 loaf.

title: scarpelli(with yeast)
directions: Boil potatoes whole in the salted water until tender.
Remove skin and mash well.
Dissolve yeast in 3 tablespoons warm water. Heat milk until hot (not boiling).
Beat eggs until lemon colored. Add shortening, salt and half of flour, beat well.
Add yeast, sugar, milk, and the rest of the flour and mix well.
Dough should be firm and spongy.
Cover and raise in a warm area for 1 hour. Fill frying pan with about an inch of oil.
Get a tablespoon of dough and stretch with fingers.
Drop in hot oil and fry until deep gold.
Drain on paper towels and roll in mixture of half powdered sugar and half granulated sugar.

title: cheese and broccoli casserole
directions: Fry onions in oleo; add broccoli and cook until thawed.
Mix in soup, cheese and rice.
Pour into baking pan and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla until thick.
Stir in baking soda, baking powder, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, pineapple, zucchini, flour, nuts and dates.

title: lluchen kugel
directions: Cream cream cheese, sugar, butter, milk, eggs and pineapple. Put cooked noodles in greased 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Pour creamed mixture over noodles.
Sprinkle with corn flake crumbs mixed with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 24 servings.

title: bean-rice casserole(supper dish)
directions: Brown onion slightly in shortening.
Add beef and brown.
Add beans and Spanish rice.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.
When done, sprinkle with cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.
Serve with green salad and French bread.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients until creamy and well blended.
Pat mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut into squaress.
Refrigerate.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix 1/2 cup of soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg, onions and sauce.
Bake in 12 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Remove meat loaf to platter.
Keep warm.
Pour rest of soup and water in pan.
Mix.
Serve over meat loaf.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes.
While still hot, peel potatoes.
Let cool. Add butter; mix well.
Add milk, sugar and eggs.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: garden relish
directions: Wash and cut vegetables in small pieces.
In a large bowl combine the tomatoes, peppers, onions, cucumbers, salt and 6 cups water.
Let stand overnight.
Next day, in medium saucepan, cook carrots, green beans and celery in slightly salted water until tender.
Drain and rinse.
Next, drain the tomato mixture and rinse it once.

title: quick bisquick cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix Bisquick, 1/2 cup sugar, Crisco and water.
Pour Bisquick mixture into greased baking dish.
Mix peaches with 1 cup sugar and vanilla; spread over Bisquick mixture.
Cut up butter on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: tangy-sweet meatballs
directions: Brown meatballs on cookie sheet in 350° oven, shaking gently to cook all sides.
Combine rest of ingredients in large saucepan. Place meatballs in sauce and simmer 1 hour.
Bite size hot dog pieces may be placed into simmering sauce.

title: turkey cutlet piccata
directions: Pound each turkey breast to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into serving size pieces if large.
Beat egg with milk on a plate.
Dip cutlets in egg, then breadcrumbs.
Saute cutlets in 4 tablespoons hot butter or margarine until browned on both sides.
Remove cutlets from pan.
Reduce heat to low.
Squeeze juice of 1/2 lemon into drippings.
Stir in bouillon, salt and 3/4 cup water until blended.
Return turkey to skillet.
Cover; simmer for 5 minutes, until tender.
Garnish with sliced lemon and parsley.

title: turkey or chicken waldorf salad
directions: Toss slightly with mayonnaise and a little of the pineapple juice.
Chill and serve.

title: orange candy cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; cream well after each.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with 3 1/2 cups of flour.
Mix remaining flour with dates, candy and nuts.
Add to batter.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Saute meat and onions, drain.
Combine cream cheese, soup, milk, ketchup and salt until smooth.
Add to meat.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Place canned biscuits on top, bake for 15 minutes to 25 minutes longer.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: This cake must be assembled 3 days ahead for crackers to become like pastry.

title: creamy chicken broccoli noodles
directions: In saucepan, cook noodles according to package directions. Add seasoning packets; drain off most of liquid.
Stir in cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Add chicken and broccoli.
Heat through, stirring often. Stir in tomatoes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Bring butter, sugar and syrup to boil. Boil for 3 minutes, bringing to soft-ball stage. Add vanilla and food coloring. Pour on popped corn. Butter hands and form into balls. Wrap individually in plastic wrap.

title: asparagus frittata
directions: In a saucepan, bring water to a boil. Add asparagus; cover and boil for 3 minutes. Drain and immediately place asparagus in ice water; drain and pat dry. In a 10-inch ovenproof skillet, saute onion in oil until tender. Add parsley and asparagus; toss to coat.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Combine flour, soda and salt and set aside.
In a large bowl combine butter, sugar and brown sugar, then add vanilla and beat.
When creamy, add eggs gradually and then add flour.
Stir in morsels and nuts by hand.
Line cookie sheets with foil, drop by teaspoons onto lined sheets and bake at 375 degrees for 8 - 10 minutes (check at around 6 - 7 minutes).
Yields about 100
2 inch cookies.

title: minestrone
directions: Melt butter in large soup kettle; saute carrots, celery, onions, garlic, and cabbage about 20 minutes; stir often.
Add tomatoes, water, rice, tomato sauce, seasonings, potatoes, bouillon cubes and zucchini.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer covered 30 minutes.
Add beans and spinach; return to a boil and cook over medium heat until spinach is cooked; add more water if needed.
Garnish with Parmesan.
Serves 9.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Place chicken in a large shallow dish.
Combine all ingredients and pour over chicken breasts.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Cook breasts on outdoor grill until done.

title: crumble pie
directions: Peel enough apples (slice thin) to fill a 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle top with some cinnamon or nutmeg.
Mix together last 5 ingredients.
Put ingredients in your hands and mix until they are crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples and bake until brown.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with milk or ice cream.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Mash potatoes.
Mix ingredients together and pour into casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with mini marshmallows to cover top. Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: turkey porcupines
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir well. Shape into 16 (1-inch) balls.
Place in a 2-quart casserole coated with vegetable cooking spray.

title: baked macaroni & cheese
directions: Beat eggs, salt and worcestershire sauce together in a medium sized bowl.
Add milk and mix thoroughly.
Layer macaroni and grated cheese in casserole dish.
Pour egg mixture over macaroni and cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees until set and lightly browned on top, about 45 - 50 minutes.

title: breakfast of champions
directions: Slightly butter 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Butter bread and chop into cubes.
Cook sausage and drain off fat.

title: peek-a-boo chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken.
Pour into large baking dish and place chicken on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours and don't peek!

title: sausage-mushroom breakfast casserole
directions: Spread croutons in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; set aside.
Cook sausage until browned and crumbled; drain well; sprinkle sausage over croutons.
Combine eggs, milk, soup and mustard; pour over sausage.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: cake icing
directions: Sift powdered sugar.
Add Crisco, eggs and vanilla; mix well.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion. Drain the grease. Add salt, pepper, garlic powder and onion powder to taste. Add the cream of mushroom soup to the meat with about 1/4 cup of water; mix together well. Set aside.

title: don't-cook-the-pasta manicotti
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat with onion and garlic.
Drain well.
Stir in 2 cups of tomato juice, tomato paste, sugar and seasonings.
Simmer while preparing filling.

title: pig picker cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 11-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: party chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, pepper and pickles.
Mix cream with mayonnaise, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Toss with chicken and refrigerate.

title: raisin pie
directions: Heat to boiling point, syrup and sugar.
Add to syrup the eggs, vanilla and butter.
Place raisins in bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Pour syrup over raisins.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: mushroom roast
directions: Dredge meat in flour and brown slowly; season with salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients, except for mushrooms.
Simmer slowly until meat is tender.
Add mushrooms just before serving. Good served with green bean casserole.

title: summer squash medley
directions: Combine oil and garlic in large skillet.
Once heated, add remainder of ingredients, except cornmeal.
Cook until tender, covered.
Add cornmeal right before serving.

title: blender lemon pie
directions: Wash lemon and remove seeds.
Cut into quarters or eighths and chop in blender, peeling included.
Add other ingredients to blender and mix until mushy, resembling a milkshake.
Pour into 2 crusts that have been baked 5 minutes.
Bake pies at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: company casserole
directions: Brown beef in 3 tablespoons butter. Stir in tomato sauce.

title: pot roast
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown roast in oil.
Spoon off fat; stir in mushroom soup, onion soup and 1 cup water.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Turn occasionally.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Cook 40 minutes or until done.
Uncover for last 20 minutes.
Remove roast and vegetables; stir together flour and remaining water to make thickener.
Stir into juice in Dutch oven.
Cook, stirring until mixture boils and thickens.

title: quick and easy chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, soup and sour cream. Place in casserole. Melt butter and mix with cracker crumbs. Sprinkle on top of chicken mixture. Bake at 400° until bubbly. Serves 4.

title: texas taters
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix everything except corn flakes and melted margarine.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle corn flakes over top; drizzle with melted margarine. Bake 1 hour.

title: southern corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Heat olive oil in large skillet; add garlic and onion and saute until transparent.
Remove stems from fresh herbs.
Add herbs, tomato sauce and water to skillet and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 4 1/2 cups.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients and place in a large baking dish. Melt margarine and mix with Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top. Bake at 300° until bubbly.
Reduce temperature slightly and bake 10 more minutes.

title: torte
directions: Cream together margarine and 1/4 cup sugar.
Mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine cream cheese, eggs and 1/2 cup white sugar in mixer; pour over crumbs.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: my favorite chocolate frosting
directions: Cook sugar, salt and milk over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
When mixture is slightly syrupy, remove from heat and add chocolate chips, marshmallows and margarine.
Beat until smooth, then spread on your favorite cake layers.
Will cover 2 to 3 layers.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon in large saucepan until crisp.
Add onions, carrots, celery and cabbage; saute 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, clam juice, tomato soup, salt, pepper, potatoes and water.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add clams and thyme.
Cook 10 minutes longer.

title: cheese-garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Mix margarine, garlic powder and chives. Brush over hot biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Serve hot.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: quick-baked pasta(family style)
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions.
Add oil to a frying pan; cook beef and garlic.
Saute until the meat is tender, then drain excess fat.
Add all remaining ingredients, except the cheese for topping and the pasta.
Simmer while pasta is cooking. Drain pasta; mix with the sauce.
Pour into a 3-quart baking dish; top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes, or until bubbly hot.
Serves 6.

title: lemon tea bread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in small saucepan; bring to boil. Remove mixture from heat; cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Cool. Beat butter with electric mixer at medium speed until creamy; gradually add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to butter mixture; begin and end with flour.
Stir in lemon rind after thoroughly mixed.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Pour Lemon Glaze over bread.

title: peach cake
directions: Mix all together well.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: pasta with fresh tomatoes
directions: Drain tomatoes in colander.
Saute onions, peppers, oregano, salt and pepper in olive oil until crisp-tender.
Stir in tomato paste, sugar, vinegar and tomatoes.
Heat through but do not boil. Serve over hot pasta.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mccray macaroni and cheese
directions: Layer ingredients, starting with macaroni and ending with cheese in a 4-quart round casserole dish.
When done with layers, cover with milk until just visible.
Bake at 375° until cheese on top is brown.
Let stand 10 minutes and then serve.

title: baked (dry) lima beans
directions: Soak dry lima beans in water overnight.
Cook (not soft).
Fry bacon until crisp; remove bacon and crumble.
In bacon fat, saute onions and chopped celery.
In other saucepan, mix molasses, catsup, mustard, sugar and salt.
Add this to beans.
Place all ingredients in baking dish.
Add crumbled bacon on top.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: 16 bean soup(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Rinse beans and add salt.
Add water and cover.
Soak 3 hours or overnight.
Drain.
Put beans in large pan.
Add water, onion, garlic, ham hocks, tomatoes and juice of lemon.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef in strips 1/2-inch thick, remove all fat.
Pat dry with paper towel.
Salt and pepper.
Melt 1 Tablespoon margarine and pam in non-stick skillet.
Add meat, cook until brown both sides.
Remove.
Saute onions, mushrooms, until tender.
Return meat.
Combine broth, mustard, bay leaf, tomato paste and pour over meat.
Cover, let simmer gently for 1/2 hour until meat is tender, remove bay leaf.
Make smooth paste of flour and water.
Stir into skillet stirring constantly until thick.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.
You can use any fruit.

title: surprise red beans and rice
directions: Put beans in a pot.
Stir them to make them taste good.
Takes a lot of hard work, but when there done, taste them to see if they are good enough.
Put beans over rice and then me and Mom will eat them.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken until tender; reserve 1 cup broth and take chicken off bone.
Place in a baking dish.
Mix chicken soup and celery soup with sour cream.
Pour over chicken.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix potatoes, milk, sugar, eggs, allspice, salt and butter. Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° until center is firm.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all together, except for Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 mixture in container and let congeal.
Put Cool Whip in middle, then pour remainder of mixture over this and congeal.

title: play dough
directions: Mix the ingredients in a pan while stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat until the dough pulls away from the pan.
Remove the dough and knead for a few minutes.
Store in plastic container or Ziploc bag.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Mixture will be very stiff. Form into small balls and bake at 350° for 15 minutes. These may be frozen and reheated.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together; form in ball.
Chill before rolling in nuts. Wrap in foil and let set for 6 to 7 hours in refrigerator.

title: florida chicken and rice
directions: Spray 2-quart casserole dish with Mazola.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In large nonstick skillet melt oleo and saute onion and bell pepper.
Put onion mixture in a large bowl and add cooked chicken, cooked wild rice, mayonnaise, green beans, soup, water chestnuts, mushrooms, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Mix.
Dump into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 5 minutes more.
Serves 8.

title: company potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes (peeled) in salted water until cooked.
Chill. Shred.
In the top of a double boiler over hot water, melt butter; add cheese, a little at a time, reserving 2 tablespoons.
Mix together sour cream and milk.
Add to cheese mixture.
Add onions and stir together.
Add to shredded potatoes.
Put mixture in a large greased casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika; bake 5 more minutes.
Serve.

title: oven barbecue
directions: Spread meat in baking pan and put in 400° oven.
Stir occasionally until done.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan and heat on top unit.
Pour over meat all together and serve on hot buns.
Reduce heat to 300° to keep barbecue ready to serve.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a medium bowl combine flour, baking soda, salt and oatmeal.
Mix well and set aside.
In a large bowl cream butter and both brown and white sugar; add vanilla and eggs. Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture and raisins. Blend until combined.
Drop by rounded tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheets, 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake 22 minutes or until light golden brown.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Combine baking powder, flour, salt, pepper, egg and cheese in a large bowl.
Add zucchini and mix well.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Drop mixture by tablespoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine orange juice, lemonade and pineapple juice; add water. Stir until blended.
Thaw strawberries just until they will separate; add to juice.
At serving time, add chilled ginger ale and pour over block of ice (or crushed ice) in punch bowl.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add remaining ingredients, in order listed, and mix until smooth.
Pour into 14 x 9-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: holiday mashed potatoes
directions: In a large mixer bowl, mash hot potatoes.
When all lumps are removed, add cream cheese in small pieces and then the butter. Beat well.
Mix in sour cream to the milk; add the eggs and onion. Add to the potato mix along with salt and pepper.
Beat well until light and fluffy.
Place in a greased 9-inch round casserole and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until lightly brown on top.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well and make into one large loaf or two small ones.
Bake in oven one hour at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Whisk all ingredients together until blended.

title: cheese dreams
directions: Split muffins in half; butter.
Toast on one side.
Cut bacon in half and broil until crisp.
Top each muffin half with thick tomato slice, 2 broiled bacon strips and cheese slice.
Return to broiler and broil 5 inches from heat until cheese melts.
Serve at once.

title: lemon scones
directions: Toss peel with 2 Tbsp. flour. Combine the rest of dry ingredients, cut in butter. Add fruit, egg, yogurt and peel. Blend well. Divide into balls, flatten into 1/2 inch thick. Bake at 350 degrees until light brown. Sprinkle with sugar on top before baking if desired.

title: quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9 to 10-inch pie or quiche plate.
Place bacon, cheese and onion on bottom of plate. Blend or whip remaining ingredients and pour over first layer. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour until golden brown.
Stick knife in center, it will come out clean if done.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: *Note:
Fresh may be used, but cooking time would vary.

title: layered taco dip
directions: In bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, spread beans over entire bottom. In a small mixing bowl combine lemon juice with mashed avocados; spread over beans.
In a bowl, combine sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning.
Spread over avocados.
Sprinkle with cheese, tomatoes, green onions and black olives.
Chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: old fashion egg custard
directions: Beat 3 egg yolks and 1 whole egg only slightly.
Add 2/3 cup sugar, flour and cornstarch which has been sifted together. Stir only to mix.
Add
hot
milk
gradually; add flavoring and butter. Pour into uncooked shell
and
bake 30 minutes at 350°. Do not preheat oven.
Do
not overcook. Cook only until filling is firm. Beat egg whites
until firm.
Add 6 tablespoons sugar gradually and beat well.
Add
1/2 teaspoon vanilla and pile on pie.
Bake 15 minutes in
oven.
Cool
completely
before cutting.

title: ginger oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Beat in egg and molasses. Mix flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and ginger together.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Add oatmeal.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown together the hamburger and chopped onion.
Drain well. Mix all ingredients together.
Add salt, pepper and a little garlic for taste.
Simmer 45 minutes to an hour.
Add grated cheese on top when serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in salt.
Brown meat.
Add garlic and onion. Cook together until almost done.
Put butter in the bottom of pan. Put noodles, then meat, then different cheeses.
Then noodles again, meat and cheese until you have it all in the pan.

title: apple salad
directions: Cook pineapple, sugar and flour until thick; remove from heat and cool.
When mixture cools, fold chopped apples into it and spread in a casserole dish.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: grandma jean's welsh cakes
directions: Set aside 1 tablespoon sugar.
Mix together remaining sugar, flour, baking powder and nutmeg.
Add butter; rub with your fingers until fine crumbs form.
Add raisins, egg white and milk; stir until dough holds together.

title: appetizer sausage ball
directions: Day Before Serving:
In large bowl, mix flour, curry, paprika, salt and cheese.
Cut in butter or margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs; with hands, press into ball.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and grate when cold.
Heat soup and butter over low heat and blend in sour cream.
In large bowl alternate potatoes, onions, cheese and sauce.
Toss lightly.
Put in 9 x 14-inch buttered dish.
Crush corn flakes and sprinkle over top of casserole (optional).
Add 2 tablespoons oleo over corn flakes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: palouse soup mix
directions: Mix one cup of mix with 4 cups of water or seasoned stock in a large pan.
Add one cup of cooked chopped meat, if desired.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and cover pan.
Simmer gently for 45 minutes or until peas are tender.
It may take longer at high altitudes or in hard water areas.
Add 1/2 teaspoon of salt if desired.

title: cool chocolate cake
directions: Mix all cake ingredients together; bake at 350° until done. Let set and cool.
Mix instant pudding together as the box tells you.
When cake is cool to touch, pour pudding over it.
Cover; refrigerate for several hours.
Serve with fruit.

title: sweet and sour sauce(for swedish meat balls)
directions: In
a
pan
put
cup chicken broth.
Stir in cornstarch. Add rest of broth, soy sauce, vinegar and corn syrup. Cook	until thickened and clear.
Add pineapple, green peppers and
cherries. Cook
for
minutes.
Pour over cooked meatballs.
Serve with steamed rice.

title: party punch
directions: Combine Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Stir until Kool-Aid and sugar are dissolved.
Add pineapple juice and stir.
Then you can cool the mixture if you like or add ice if serving immediately. Add the ginger ale just before serving.
Makes about 50 servings.

title: chow-chow
directions: Add the pickling spice and salt to the water in a small pot. Bring to a boil and let boil for 10 minutes.
Mix all the remaining ingredients together in a large pot and add the spiced water, pouring it through a strainer.
Let cook slowly for 35 to 45 minutes, stirring often.
Taste for seasoning.
Store in sterile half-pint jars or refrigerate.
Makes about 12 small jars.

title: meat casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Set aside.
Saute onions, bell pepper and meat.
Add soup, mushrooms and spaghetti sauce.
Layer Pyrex baking dish with half of noodles, half of sauce and half of cheese.
Repeat layer.
Bake for approximately 45 minutes at 350°.
Be sure it is hot and bubbly.
May use less cheese, if desired.

title: candied dill pickle
directions: Mix pickle with other ingredients.
Let set at room temperature.
Stir night and morning for 3 days.
Put back in jar. Refrigerate.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Step One:
Heat cheese and butter in double boiler until melted; mix well.

title: t.v. snacks
directions: Combine
ingredients,
tossing gently until mixed thoroughly. Spread in baking
pan.
Cover
and bake at 250° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake at 250° for 1 more hour.

title: no bake honey bars
directions: Grind raisins and nuts.
Stir in honey.
Press onto sheet pan to layer 1/2-inch thick.
Cover; refrigerate 24 hours.
Cut into bars.
Roll in white or colored coconut.

title: hollywood pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Beat in eggs.
Add milk and butter. Cook on top of stove until thick.
Pour in graham cracker crust. Beat egg whites until standing in peaks.
Put on pie.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top.
Brown in oven.

title: squash pie
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Cream margarine; add to squash. Beat egg yolks with sugar until creamy; add to squash and beat again.
Add vanilla, pineapple and flour and blend well.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Beat egg whites, put on top of squash mixture and brown in oven.

title: blond brownies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt together.
In a large saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in brown sugar and remove from heat; cool 10 minutes.
Add eggs, beating well.
Stir in flour mixture, nuts and chocolate chips; blend well.
Spread in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking sheet which has been greased and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool, cut and enjoy.

title: grandma b's sausage stuffing
directions: Fry hot sausage and mild sausage until done.
Do not drain. Fry onion, margarine and celery until tender and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix sausage mixture, onion mixture and bread mixture, then add eggs, hot milk, hot water and broth.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peek-a-boos
directions: Heat the butter and chocolate chips over medium heat in a heavy saucepan until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Add the milk and stir until well blended and smooth.
Add the vanilla and flour and mix very well.
The bottom of the mixture will pull away from the sides of the pan and will look like one large "glob."
Take a small tablespoon of dough and roll into a ball in the palm of your hand. Push a Kiss, Hug or chocolate star into the center of the ball of dough.
Pull the dough up around until candy is covered.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 6 minutes.
Do not overbake!

title: corn pie
directions: Mix crumbs and melted butter.
Set aside 1/2 cup crumbs.
With spoon, press remaining crumbs into 9-inch pie tin to form a shell. In a saucepan, mix 1 cup milk, corn, salt, pepper and onion. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.
Blend flour and 1/4 cup milk.
Stir into hot mixture and cook, stirring, until thickened.
Cool slightly.
Gradually add eggs, stirring vigorously.
Pour into lined pan and sprinkle with reserved crumbs and paprika.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cut and serve.

title: sand cake
directions: Beat pudding with milk at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In separate bowl, cream together cream cheese, butter and confectioners sugar.
Mix pudding mixture with cream cheese mixture.

title: elephant stew(serves 3800 people)
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces.
This will take about 2 months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene fire for about 4 weeks at 465°.
If you expect more than 3800 people, 2 rabbits may be added, but do this only if necessary, as some people do not like to find a hare in their stew.

title: grandmom's fudge
directions: Combine sugar,
Parkay and milk in a heavy large pan (5 or 6-quart).
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Then cook over medium
heat
for 5 minutes after coming to a boil, stirring constantly
to
keep
it
from sticking to bottom of pan. Drop a little
in
cold
water.
It
will
form
a soft ball. Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate bits.
When melted, stir in Marshmallow Creme. Add vanilla.
Pour into lightly buttered pans.
Will set as it cools.

title: muffin splits
directions: Split and toast English muffins.
Spread mixture on top, clear to the edge.
Cut in fourths and broil until it bubbles.
Will do up to 9 muffins (72 pieces).

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry until brown the first 4 ingredients.
Then add the rest. Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: friendship cake
directions: Combine ingredients at room temperature in a glass jar with a loose cover.
Stir several times the first day, then once a week after that.
At the end of 2 weeks, the starter will have fermented enough to begin the steps of the Friendship Cake mix.

title: lemon ice cream
directions: Combine lemon juice
and
sugar.
Stir well.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Add lemon rind, whipping cream and milk.	Mix well. Pour mixture
into 1 gallon size freezer can and follow manufacturer's instructions.
To keep, freeze immediately.	It will stay rather soft.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: strawberry delite
directions: Crumble angel food cake.
Mix Cool Whip, sour cream, sugar and evaporated milk by hand.
Add cake pieces and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch dish.

title: oatmeal bread for bread machine
directions: In bread machine pan, place ingredients in order given. Select "white bread" setting.
Bake according to bread machine directions.

title: fresh corn pudding(serves 6)
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients, stirring well.
Combine egg and skim milk; add corn mixture.
Spoon mixture into a 1-quart casserole dish coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: country chicken and rice
directions: Cook chicken in 1 tablespoon oil in skillet 5 to 7 minutes. Stir in undrained tomatoes, broth and 1/2 cup water. Bring to boil. Stir in corn, peas and rice. Cover and remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes.

title: florida pork chops
directions: Trim fat from chops and put into shallow baking dish. Combine other ingredients and pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; baste every 15 minutes.
If necessary, add water into pan to prevent burning.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Add well-beaten eggs with flour. Roll in balls and flatten with a glass.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: bean casserole
directions: Drain pork and kidney beans.
Cook limas as directed on package and drain.	Mix all ingredients except bacon and place in a baking dish.
Cover with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Approximately 12 servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, water and Karo in a heavy skillet until it will spin a thread.
Add peanuts and cook until they make a popping sound.
Take off heat and add oleo and soda.
Stir well.
Spread on a greased cookie sheet.
When cooled, break into pieces and store in an airtight container.

title: fried potato patties
directions: Mash potatoes with a fork until soft.
Add milk and mix well. Add egg and dry ingredients until well blended.
Fry until golden brown, turn and brown the other side.
Yields 4 servings.

title: hawaiian chicken breasts
directions: Combine pineapple juice, ketchup, brown sugar, margarine, vinegar, cornstarch, salt, chili powder, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce in 2-quart microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on full power 4 to 5 minutes, stirring every minute.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken. Cover with foil and bake
in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 30 minutes, basting occasionally, if needed.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Fill to rim in freezer with milk.
Beat eggs until light; add sugar.
Beat until mixture gets thick; add rest of ingredients. Pour into freezer.

title: chicken quiche
directions: Prick crust and bake at 400° for 3 minutes.
Remove from oven; prick again, then bake 5 minutes longer.
Cool.
Place chicken, pimento and cheese in bottom of shell.
Combine eggs, half and half, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour in shell and bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes or until set.

title: one-bowl brownies
directions: Melt chocolate; stir in sugar until well blended.
Stir in eggs and vanilla until completely mixed.
Mix in flour until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes 24 brownies.

title: butternut snowballs
directions: Place the butter, sugar, salt and vanilla into the mixing bowl, fitted with the paddle attachment.
Mix on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Stop the machine and scrape down the bowl.
Add the flour and mix on low speed just until combined.
Stop the machine and scrape down the bowl.
Add the walnuts and mix on low speed just until combined.

title: jill's chocolate cake
directions: Mix together.
Batter will be very runny.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: e z & fluffy cheesecake
directions: Prepare crust per box instructions.
Combine cheese cake filling per box adding the cream cheese, Cool Whip and vanilla. Pour into prepared crust and chill.
May be served plain or with fruit topping of choice.

title: brownies
directions: Cream sugar, margarine, vanilla and egg.
Mix flour and cocoa together, then add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in (small) 13 x 9-inch pan at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool about 1 hour. Icing may be added after they cool.

title: cheesy potatoes(crock-pot)
directions: Grease a crock-pot with margarine or spray. Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Put in crock-pot and cook 1 hour on High and up to 3 hours on low, stirring after first hour.

title: chicken cheese casserole
directions: Boil chicken and cut into bite-size pieces.
Boil noodles in chicken broth until done.
Mix all soup, chicken, noodles, picante sauce and cheese together.
Stir until well mixed.
Simmer until heated.
Serve.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Sift flour.
Measure and add soda and salt.
Sift again.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Mix.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet, spaced 2 to 3 inches apart.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: creme de menthe cookies
directions: In pan on
stove melt 1/2 cup butter or margarine.
Mix in cocoa powder;
blend
well.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/2 cup powdered sugar, egg and
vanilla.
Stir
graham cracker crumbs in. Mix well.	Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: spiced grape juice (hot)
directions: Tie spices in a bag.
Coffee filters work well.
Put bag into saucepan with the grape juice and sugar.
Bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Add lemon and orange juices.
Serve hot.

title: crock-pot beef burritos
directions: Cut beef into 1-inch cubes.
Roll in seasoned flour.
Fry until brown in 1 tablespoon oil.
Meanwhile, in measuring cup, empty tomato sauce and chili
mix.
Fill with water to make 2 cups total. Mix meat and sauce mixture in crock-pot.
Cook on medium-low several hours until meat is tender.
Spoon into tortillas and cheese and roll.
Top tortilla with sauce and more cheese. Microwave to melt cheese.

title: good potatoes
directions: Mix everything together in a large bowl, except the hash browns. Take the frozen hash browns and break into small pieces (while still in the bag), then add to the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bubbly in the middle.

title: party punch
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Place scoops of sherbet into punch.
Fruit slices can be added.
To keep punch cold, make cubes from punch.

title: hankie pankies
directions: Brown meats and drain.
Add cheese and spices.
Heat until cheese melts.
Place one tablespoon of mixture on slice of bread or Triscuit.
When ready to serve, place under broiler until brown.

title: gramm's crab salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Fold in orange slices.
Chill.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar, rice crispies, set aside.
Melt chocolate & paraffin.
Roll ingredients into balls.
Put on toothpicks and dip in chocolate.
Place on wax paper.
Refrigerate for 2 hours

title: preserved husband
directions: Be very careful when you make your selection.
Do not choose too young and take only such varieties as have been reared in good moral atmosphere.
When once decided upon and selected, let that part remain forever settled and give your entire attention to preparation for safekeeping.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Place pie filling in 10-inch pie pan.
Top with nuts. Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Serve warm.
Spoon into serving dishes; top with Reddi-Wip.

title: kirsten's favorite
directions: Put whipping cream and marshmallows in a bowl in the fridge overnight.
Beat the next day until thick, then add fruit.
Cover it and refrigerate.

title: walking salad
directions: Spread peanut butter and raisins on a lettuce leaf.
Roll the leaf up.
Voila!
Walking Salad.

title: jeanne's holiday punch recipe
directions: Mix all liquids together.
Then add strawberries and orange sherbet. Stir.
Serve and enjoy.

title: aileen beever's potato soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add celery, carrot, potatoes and water.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add pimiento and Milnot.
Heat, but do not boil.
Add salt and pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage; scramble the eggs and grate the cheese.
Layer sausage, eggs, cheese and picante mixture on top of 1 can crescent rolls, which are rolled out in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Then top the mixture with the other can of crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° until rolls are done.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown meat; drain well.
Stir in taco seasoning mix.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Combine meat and remaining ingredients in a large salad bowl.
Toss well.
Serve with dressing.

title: lazy man's casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package directions. Brown beef, onion and bell pepper.
Add spaghetti seasoning, tomato paste and water.
In large casserole dish, combine beef mixture with macaroni and cheese.
Add corn.
Bake in oven until well heated.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: delicious chocolate cake
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan.
Add oil and sugar.
Add cocoa, flour and water.
Mix. Add eggs (slightly beaten).
Add soda to buttermilk and mix with rest of ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Mix. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
While still warm, ice cake.

title: easy goulash
directions: Use beef and macaroni according to your family's needs.
Cook macaroni; drain and set aside.
In skillet, brown and drain beef. Add onion, bell pepper and seasonings.
Add tomatoes and juice. Simmer 30 minutes.
Pour over macaroni mix and serve.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs and syrup.
Stir until well blended.
Add butter and stir until well mixed.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake about 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: turkey cheddar casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Cook broccoli; drain and dice.

title: apple-orange punch
directions: Mix juices together.
Just before serving, add ginger ale. Spoon in sherbet.
Makes 28 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: In large kettle, combine vinegar, sweetener, salt, celery seed, mustard seed and turmeric.
Bring to the boil.
Remove from heat and add the vegetables.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Heat to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.
Ladle into clean, hot jars and seal.
Makes 4 1/2 pints.

title: grandma k's cherry divinity
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, syrup and water.
Cook to hard ball stage, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water and vanilla together. Cut bananas in small slices.
Add banana and blend until well mixed.
Add pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done in a greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: ham and cheese appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 350.
Grease rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2.
Mix all ingredients, spread in pan. Bake until golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into rectangles, about 2 x 1 1/2 inches.
Makes 36 appetizers.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Marinate chicken 6 to 8 hours. Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: potato-cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine potatoes, broccoli, celery, carrot, onion, parsley, broth mix, pepper and 1 cup water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes.

title: chicken lebey
directions: Salt and pepper chicken strips as desired.
In large pot brown chicken strips in mixture of butter and olive oil.
Add drained water chestnut slices and liquid ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice, then spoon Hollandaise Sauce over each serving. Serves 4 to 6.

title: roasted garlic spread
directions: Peel outer skin from garlic; leave head intact.
Place garlic in a small baking pan.
Drizzle with oil.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 8 to 10 additional minutes or until garlic is soft.
Remove from oven and let cool completely.
Remove and discard papery skin from garlic. Scoop out garlic pulp with a small spoon.

title: ham casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to directions. Mix ham, rice, celery, eggs, onion, mushroom soup, corn flakes, almonds and mayonnaise. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: magic cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: chicken tortilla ole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: *Prepare whole chicken; place breast side down in microwave-safe dish with lid.
Microwave on High power for 15 minutes.
Turn over.
Microwave 25 minutes on Medium power (50%). Uncover; allow to cool and remove from bones.

title: browned onion potato soup
directions: Quarter sliced onion.
Brown onion in deep pan in bacon grease.
When browned, add 2 tablespoons of flour and brown lightly.
Then add water.
Add potatoes that have been sliced and halved.
Season to taste.
Boil 10 minutes, then simmer until potatoes are cooked.
Serve.

title: hamburger delight
directions: Mix ground beef, bread and egg all together and make 4 patties.
Brown in skillet.
Cover with mushroom soup and simmer.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Rub both sides of meat with garlic and cut into 1 1/2 x 1-inch strips.
Coat meat with flour and seasonings and brown in shortening.
Add onion, soup and water and simmer covered for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until meat is tender.
Remove cover and add mushrooms and continue to cook until thickened.
Add sour cream and chives and blend.
Serve over noodles.

title: baked mashed potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients with a mixer until fluffy.
Put into a casserole.
(May be made day before and warmed in oven.) Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken.
Debone and cut into chunks.
Cook spaghetti in broth.
Saute onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic clove in butter.
Add tomato sauce, mushroom soup, mushrooms, sugar, salt and pepper. Mix with the spaghetti and chicken.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Add bananas and sour cream.
Sift together and add dry ingredients. Place in greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: libby's hot wings
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Roll in mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Deep fry drumettes in hot oil until brown on both sides; drain.
Place in baking pan.
Pour hot wing sauce over drumettes. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serve with Ranch dressing.
Yields 60 servings.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand. Pour into greased and floured 15 x 10 sheet pan. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: citrus slaw
directions: Combine mayo, orange juice concentrate, sugar, salt and pepper. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Chill.
Makes 5 cups.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Do not stir!
Microwave on High for 2 minutes; then mix well. Add vanilla to the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into pan; put in fridge for 45 minutes to an hour.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first four ingredients real well. Add flour, salt and milk.
Mix real well.
The longer you mix, the better.
Add flavorings and mix well.
Bake for 1 hour or maybe a little longer, depending on the oven.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Mix all ingredients in large casserole.
Top with Velveeta cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans and spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix as directed.
Soften margarine and cream cheese. Mix with powdered sugar.
Spread over cake mixture.
Bake for approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix ingredients, except carrots, and boil for 2 minutes.
Add to carrots and let stand overnight.
Good hot or cold as salad.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix well and form into balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Place in sauce and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Mix together.
Grease and flour 3 pans and pour in pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Let cool.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Mix cranberry sauce and 1 cup boiling water with blender until smooth. Mix Jell-O and 1 cup boiling water; add to cranberry sauce and add pecans. Pour 1/2 mixture into pan. Let it set until firm, about 1 hour. Spread sour cream; add rest of mixture and refrigerate until firm. Cut into squares.

title: neapolitan calamari
directions: Wash squid and pat dry.
Cut squid into 1/4 inch slices.
Heat oil in 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat.
Cook garlic in oil, stirring frequently, until golden.
Stir in tomatoes, chili and squid.
Cook uncovered 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat to medium. Cover and cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
(Do not overcook or squid will be tough.)
To serve, spoon liquid in skillet over each serving.

title: oklahoma beans
directions: Cook beans until done.
Drain.
Saute onions.
Brown meat and drain off grease.
Add meat to beans; add other ingredients; cover with lid and simmer about 2 hours.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Grease	two
8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Combine applesauce, shortening and
sugar
in
saucepan.
Bring to boil and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool.
Mix fruits and nuts in a large
bowl.
Sift	together
flour, soda, salt and spices. Gradually
stir into fruit mixture.
Stir in the cooled applesauce mixture.
Pour
into
prepared
pans
and bake in a 300° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pans for about 30 minutes, then remove from
pans and cool completely. Wrap and store in tightly covered container.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and apples. Let stand.
Measure all ingredients. Mix with apples and sugar.
Put in shallow pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: one pan crazy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and baking soda into an ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Make three holes in flour-cocoa mixture with back of spoon.
In first hole, pour oil.
In second hole, pour vinegar.
In third hole, pour vanilla. Pour 1 cup water over all and stir with fork.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin spice bread
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour.

title: fat free banana-orange slush
directions: After ice cubes have been pureed, add banana, orange juice and vanilla.
Blend for 20 seconds.
Pour into glass and sweeten to taste.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: peas and water chestnuts
directions: Mix all ingredients, saving 1/2 can onions for top the last 5 minutes of baking time. Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add liquids. Cut cranberries in half and add with nuts and orange rind to batter.
Bake in lightly greased loaf pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: diabetic hawaiian pie
directions: Drain pineapple.
Remove juice.
Add sugar and flour to juice. Cook until thickened.
Let cool and fold in pineapple and sliced bananas.
Pour in pie crust.
Sprinkle nuts over all.
Then sprinkle coconut.
Chill 2 hours.
Cover with Cool Whip. Delicious

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix, Milnot and melted butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 5 minutes in a greased, floured 9 x 13 pan.
Cook caramels and 1/3 c. Milnot over low heat until caramels are melted.
Pour over cake.
Combine chocolate chips and pecans and spread over top of cake.
Dot cake with butter and place a pecan half on each butter dot.
Bake 25 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Zucchini may be chopped in blender or grated.
Mix together all ingredients.
(Mix in nuts and squash last.)
Pour into 2 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O by direction;
add
pineapple and cherry pie filling and let "set"
in refrigerator.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese
and
sugar.
Spread
this on top of the set Jell-O and sprinkle nuts on top.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Mix frozen whipped topping, milk and lemon juice; blend well. Fold in strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: Beat egg yolks in large mixer bowl until light.
Add sugar gradually, beating until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in brandy, rum, milk, 3 cups whipped cream and vanilla.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar in mixer bowl until stiff peaks form.
Fold into egg yolk mixture.
Pour into punch bowl.
Sweeten whipped cream with confectioners sugar.
Ladle eggnog into punch cups; top with whipped cream and sprinkle of nutmeg.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: steak cantonese and rice
directions: Slice meat into thin strips, cutting diagonally across the grain.
Brown steak in oil over high heat.
Reduce heat.
Stir in tomatoes, green peppers, soy sauce and seasonings.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Blend in cornstarch.
Serve over rice.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix until well blended.
Use 2 or 3 teaspoons mix for 1 cup cocoa, filling cup with boiling water.
Serves 35.

title: deviled ham and cheese log
directions: Blend ham with pecans, cream cheese and seasoning; shape into log roll.
Chill.
Sprinkle paprika on waxed paper and roll log evenly with paprika.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill overnight to blend flavors well.
Slice and serve on crackers or party rye. Makes 24 servings.

title: jim dandy muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and spice.
Cut in shortening until particles are fine.
Add milk and egg.
Mix just until thoroughly blended.
Spoon into greased muffin cups.
Place 1 teaspoon jam or jelly on top of each muffin pressing into batter slightly.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts if desired.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: hot dog
directions: Wieners can be chunked up or left whole.
Mix all ingredients, except wieners.
Bring to a boil.
Add wieners and simmer.

title: chocolate waffles
directions: Preheat waffle iron; grease lightly.
Sift flour, cocoa, sugar, baking powder and salt into a large bowl.
Combine milk, eggs, oil and vanilla in a small bowl.
Stir liquid ingredients into dry ingredients until moistened.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Make cornbread (2 cup batch); crumble cornbread in bottom of pan, 6 x 8.
Pour pinto beans with juice over cornbread.
Layer on chopped medium onion, chopped bell pepper and chopped tomatoes. Mix mayo and dill pickle juice.
Pour over casserole and let set 30 minutes.
Crumble cooked bacon on top.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onion and salt until done in small amount of water. Drain off excess water and mash. Add egg and bread crumbs. Put into greased casserole and cover with grated cheese. Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: crab casserole
directions: Combine crabmeat, mayonnaise and milk and set aside.
In skillet brown celery, diced onion and green pepper in butter.
Add to crabmeat mixture.
Add about 2 shots of Tabasco sauce and several squirts of soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Add enough cracker crumbs to make mixture thick enough to bake.
Top with additional cracker crumbs and dot generously with butter.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes, until brown and bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Grate cheese on top, if desired.

title: quick quiche
directions: Spread ham, cheese and onion over bottom of quiche dish or pie
plate.
Then, place remaining ingredients in blender. Cover and
blend at high speed for 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour this blender mixture
over
ingredients
in
pie
plate.
Bake
in preheated 350°
oven
for
to 55 minutes or until a knife inserted in the middle comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ice cream cones cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare the cake mix according to package instructions.

Fill cones about half full with cake batter and place on baking sheet, not allowing them to touch one another. Bake in preheated oven for approximately 25 minutes, or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Allow to cool completely. While cakes are cooling, prepare frosting.

title: rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Put washed rice in 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour in the milk.
Add sugar, salt and cinnamon and stir well.
Bake for 3 hours in slow oven.
Stir every 15 minutes during first hour to keep rice from staying in the bottom of casserole dish.

title: cathedral cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips and margarine.
Stir to blend. Stir in eggs until mixture is smooth.
Pour over marshmallows; mix until all marshmallows are coated. Chill about 1 hour; stir occasionally.
Form into 3 rolls about 11-inches long on waxed paper. Chill about 30 minutes.
Roll in nuts. Wrap in waxed paper and chill overnight.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: karo crazy crunch
directions: Mix
popped
corn
and	broken nuts in a large buttered pan, such as roaster or dishpan.
Combine sugar, margarine and Karo syrup
in
a
1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.	Boil, stirring occasionally, 10
to 15 minutes, or until mixture turns a light caramel color.
Remove from heat.	Stir in vanilla.
Pour over popped corn and
nuts. Mix
to
coat
well.
Spread
to
dry.
Break apart.
Store
in tightly
covered
container.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix ingredients in the order they are listed.
Grease and flour a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Cook for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325° or until top is golden brown.

title: mayonnaise dressing for salads
directions: Blend with wire whip.
Pour over salad.
Toss and serve.
Good for cole slaw.

title: baked italian spaghetti
directions: Cook onion and beef in oil, stirring, until lightly browned. Add tomato sauce, tomato juice and spices.
Simmer until thickened. Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix spaghetti with the meat mixture and half the cheese.
Spread into a baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly. Makes 6 servings.

title: cornflake wreath(for christmas)
directions: Heat margarine until melted (I use a double boiler).
Add marshmallows and melt them.
Add a few drops of green food coloring, until you have the proper shade.
Add cornflakes and stir carefully until they are well coated.
Form into wreath on wax paper.
Decorate with red cherries.
Cool and enjoy.

title: baked ziti
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Oil or butter the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix real good and make into small balls.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Arrange berries in pie shell.
Bring water, sugar and cornstarch to a boil and cool until thick.
Remove from heat and immediately add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Pour over berries; chill.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: julie's refresher course
directions: In large salad bowl, combine all ingredients except dressing. Add Ranch dressing and toss gently.
Makes 4 main dish or 8 side dish servings.

title: tearoom tortilla soup
directions: In a skillet, saute the oil, onions and garlic.
Chop the stewed tomatoes in a food processor.
Pour onions and garlic into large saucepan and add remaining ingredients and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Just before serving, add 16 to 20 slices corn tortillas. Serve with Cheddar cheese grated on top.

title: angel bars
directions: Stir all ingredients together and pour into greased 10x15 jelly roll pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350 degrees. While warm glaze with powdered sugar frosting.

title: cucumber seafood plate
directions: Run cold water over peas to thaw.
Halve cantaloupe crosswise to remove and discard seeds.
Cut cantaloupe into 9 thin slices. Halve the cucumber lengthwise.
Scoop out and discard seeds; thinly slice cucumber.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add sugar and vinegar in equal amounts, if used.
Chill and serve.
Makes 8 servings, about 4 cups.

title: chicken divine
directions: Cook broccoli. Put in greased casserole. Place chicken on top. Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown onion and garlic in oil.
Add beef, salt and pepper; brown.
Add mushrooms, tomato sauce, tomatoes and oregano.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Cook lasagne noodles as directed on package.
Arrange in large buttered baking dish a layer of noodles, meat sauce and cheese until the ingredients are used up, ending with cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar cookies
