directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add beaten eggs, vanilla, and salt. Sift flour, soda, baking powder. Roll into balls. Drop in sugar and press down with a glass dipped in sugar.

title: dominic's spinach
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in butter until onion is translucent. Let cool slightly.
In big bowl, mix spinach, eggs and cheese.
Add onion mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put in an ovenproof 8 x 12-inch glass dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and margarine until tender.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz.
Blend well and add rice and broccoli.
Pour into a buttered casserole.
Bake, covered, first half of time, then uncovered for the remaining time.
Takes about 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: turtle cake (like turtle candy)
directions: Prepare cake mix using package directions. Pour half the batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine, butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Add vanilla.
Gradually add flour, beating until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping (dry).
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not preheat oven.

title: red and white chicken cutlets
directions: Beat eggs and dip chicken cutlets into egg and then into bread crumbs.
Fry cutlets in oil.
After turning cutlets, place a slice of roasted pepper and a slice of cheese on cutlet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover 1 minute to melt cheese and serve.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, water and cornstarch together.
Cook over medium heat until mixture begins to thicken.
Remove from heat.
Add jello and food coloring.
Let cool.
Stir in strawberries.
Pour into pie shells.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Peel oranges.
Put peelings and cranberries through grinder. Section oranges.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add lemon juice, sugar and salt.
Add to oranges and cranberries, celery and pineapple and pecan mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into 10-cup mold. Chill overnight.

title: greek casserole dinner(mousaka kreas)
directions: In a frypan, brown meat slowly with the oil and sage.
Cook potatoes in 1 cup boiling water, in a covered saucepan for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Toss with salt and pepper and half can of French fried onions.
Prepare sauce mix using 1 3/4 cups water.
Arrange layers of potatoes, meat and sauce in a 2-quart buttered casserole dish, ending with sauce.
Cover dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Add remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: diabetic pumpkin pie
directions: Crust:
Mix flour and salt together.
Drizzle corn oil over this.
Mix well.
Add cold water.
Shape into pan and cool.

title: liver pate
directions: In a small pot, soften gelatin in 1/4 cup beef broth for 5 minutes.
Add the rest of the broth and heat until gelatin is dissolved completely.
Pour 1/3 cup into a one-quart mold; add Gravy Master.
Refrigerate so it sets while you prepare the rest of the ingredients.
This will give the top of the mold an attractive contrasting color.

title: easy processor biscuits
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl.
Add flour and butter.
Top with cover and process, pulsing 6 to 7 times, until mixture resembles coarse meal.
With processor running, slowly add buttermilk through food chute until the dough forms a ball, leaving sides of bowl.

title: broccoli balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll
into small balls.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° until lightly browned, about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients to form a dough.
Shape into roll and freeze or chill in refrigerator.
Slice thin and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: white fluff icing
directions: Place all ingredients, except vanilla, in the top of a double boiler.
Beat with mixer at high speed over boiling water until icing stands in soft peaks when you lift the beaters out of the icing (about 4 minutes).
Remove from the boiling water and mix a few strokes more.

title: devil wings
directions: You will need 1 two gallon resealable freezer bag.

title: lasagna rolls
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Brown beef in skillet; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce; simmer for 5 minutes.
Drain noodles.
On each noodle, spread 1/4 cup meat sauce; top with 1 to 2 tablespoons cheese.
Carefully roll up noodle and place, seam side down, in a 9 x 9-inch dish.
Spoon remaining sauce over each roll.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter, bread crumbs and chicken. Wash breast and wipe dry; dip in mixture. Put in pan and cover, let set in refrigerator overnight. Roll in bread crumbs. Place in shallow pan so that pieces don't touch. Pour butter over top. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: herb crackers
directions: Mix together oil, dressing mix and spices.
Pour over crackers.
Stir to coat evenly.
Put in airtight container.
Stir occasionally.
Ready after 4 to 6 hours.

title: cucumber dressing
directions: In blender combine cottage cheese and mayonnaise; puree until smooth.
In medium bowl combine cottage cheese mixture, cucumber, yogurt, onion and dill weed until well blended.
Add salt to taste and buttermilk.
Contains 12 calories per tablespoon.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all the canned fruit and thaw the strawberries. Put oranges, peaches and pears in a bowl; sprinkle dry pudding mix over the fruit. Pour thawed strawberries over the fruit and pudding mixture. Refrigerate overnight or at least 4 hours. Before serving, fold in sliced bananas.

title: potatoes au gratin with shrimp
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Boil in salted water until tender. Saute onions, peppers and shrimp in butter until shrimp are pink (about 15 minutes). Add milk, mushroom soup and cheeses. Cook until cheeses are melted.
Put potatoes in a casserole dish and pour cheese mixture over it.
Mix and serve.

title: gail's mushroom rolls
directions: Open rolls; leave in squares.
Mix other ingredients together, except pecans.
Spread filling over rolls.
Roll up; cut 6 to 8 pieces per square.
Roll in crushed pecans.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: avocado mold
directions: Oil mold.
Prepare lime gelatin according to package directions.
Dissolve plain gelatin in small amount of cold water; chill until partially set.
Blend together the rest of the ingredients, except the cucumber and parsley, then gently mix into the chilled gelatins.
Pour into prepared mold.
Chill until set. Serve on bed of leaf lettuce and garnish with sliced cucumber and parsley.

title: haystack candy
directions: In medium saucepan over
low
heat
melt chips.
Remove from heat and stir in
noodles and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Allow to set until hardened.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in Italian dressing at least 1 hour (3 hours or more if possible).
Roll chicken in Rice Krispies and cheese mixture.
Place in baking dish (metal or Pyrex) and drizzle melted margarine over breaded chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: auntie's chicken
directions: Season chicken with Tony Chachere seasoning and marinate. Melt and blend margarine, chopped garlic, soy sauce and Italian salad dressing with olive oil.
Pour over chicken in a large baking pan.
Slice 1/2 onion.
Spread on chicken and bake in 450° oven about 1 hour or until done.
Turn often while cooking.
tags: Italian salad dressing with olive oil

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes coarsely in a large bowl of ice water.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Mix beaten eggs, onion, flour and seasonings in a large bowl.
Drain potatoes and pat dry.
Stir 4 cups potatoes into egg mixture.
Pour by 1/4 cup into 1/8-inch deep hot oil. Fry for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: cabbage and rice
directions: In large skillet saute onion and cabbage in butter.
When tender add the beef consomme.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice.
Cover; cook until rice is done, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chile bean stew
directions: Steam carrots (peeled and sliced) and green beans over a small amount of water until tender; reserve water.
In a large skillet, brown hamburger; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients and reserved water; simmer, uncovered, about 20 minutes until flavors have blended and soup has thickened.

title: john's pumpkin cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and stir until smooth.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle sifted cake mix over top. Slice butter over top of cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over all.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or whipped topping.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter or margarine in microwave.
Mix in remaining ingredients and put in tube cake pan.
Decorate cake in seasonal way for Halloween, Thanksgiving or Christmas, etc.
Enjoy the cake.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix the ground chuck, bell pepper, onion, eggs, flour, Dale sauce and cracker crumbs together.
Shape in loaf.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Mix the tomato sauce, ketchup and mustard together; pour over meat loaf.
Continue cooking for an additional 10 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, pecans and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in a 9-inch square pan, stirring often.
Let cool.
Combine strawberries, sugar, lemon juice and egg whites. Beat at high speed on mixer for about 20 minutes or until light and fluffy.
Fold whipped cream into strawberries.
Remove 1/3 of crumbs from pan.
Pat remaining crumbs into smooth layer.
Pour strawberry mixture over crumbs in pan and sprinkle reserved crumbs over top.
Freeze.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: tiger butter
directions: Combine white chocolate and peanut butter in top of double boiler.
Bring water to a boil.
Cook over low heat until melted, stirring constantly.
Pour on cookie sheet (covered with waxed paper).
Pour melted semi-sweet chocolate over peanut butter mixture.
Swirl knife through it to make design.
Chill until firm.
Cut into pieces.

title: elegant vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook vegetables according to directions and drain.
Mix soups and milk.
Place vegetables in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour soup mixture over vegetables.
Top with crumbs. Sprinkle broken onion rings over top of crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate swiss cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Make in 3 layers.

title: flan de leche
directions: Mix all ingredients, using electric beater for 3 to 4 minutes. Bake at 325° to 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour or until light brown on top.

title: karen's fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in an 8 x 11-inch casserole dish.
In separate bowl, mix flour, 1 cup of sugar and baking powder.
Pour over butter mixture in casserole dish.
Add peaches or other fresh fruit.
Sprinkle 1 cup of sugar over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: skillet barbecue chicken
directions: Combine in large skillet over medium heat.
Add 2 pounds chicken.
Cook approximately 35 minutes, turning occasionally. Take lid off last 10 minutes.

title: recipe for happiness
directions: Take two heaping cups of patience

title: touchdown roast beef spread
directions: In a mixer bowl, beat cream cheese, mayonnaise, mustard and horseradish with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Fold in beef, radishes and green onion.
Cover and chill mixture several hours or overnight.
Serve with bread or crackers.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: western goulash
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a skillet and cook until onion is clear and hamburger is browned.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients, transferring to large pot.
Cook on low until heated through.
Salt and pepper to taste.
The taste of this dish can be changed by adding different seasonings.
You can try chili powder, beef bouillon, bay leaf, oregano or just get creative.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs thoroughly.
Remove from heat and let stand until cool.
Peel eggs and split lengthwise.
Remove yellow yolks from each egg.
Lay egg white on a plate, hollow side up.

title: homemade eggnog
directions: In a large mixing bowl beat egg whites until fluffy.
In separate bowl beat yolks until consistent.
Begin adding sugar to yolks and blend.
Add whipping cream, milk and bourbon and blend. Fold in egg whites.
Blend and serve.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Debone chicken and cut meat into bite-size pieces.
Combine everything, except potato chips.
Sprinkle chips over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Rinse in cold water; drain well.
In a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, vinegar, sugar and seasonings.
In a large bowl, combine pasta, dressing and remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate. Serves 12.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Mash boiled potatoes.
Add butter, cream cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Blend thoroughly.
Spread into casserole and garnish with paprika if desired.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: pancake mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour 1/4 cup of batter in pan or on griddle for each pancake.
Cook until bubbles form and just start to pop on top surface and edges appear dry.
Flip pancakes with spatula to lightly brown other side.
Makes 8 or 9 pancakes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In mixing bowl, beat together milk, eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla extract.
Stir in cubed bread.
Pour mixture into 1-quart baking dish, greased with vegetable shortening or oil.
Sprinkle nutmeg over top.
Put 1-inch of hot water in a large pan and set filled baking dish in it.
Bake 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve hot or cold.

title: nut covered sweet potato balls
directions: Season hot sweet potatoes with butter, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add cornflakes and sugar.
Shape into 8 balls; roll in chopped pecans.
Chill at least 30 minutes.
Arrange on pineapple slices in buttered baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Combine butter, honey and water in small saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently until boiling.
Boil 1 minute.
Spoon over potato balls.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: corn flake crunchies
directions: Bring first 2 ingredients to a boil until sugar melts.
Then mix in a mixing bowl the corn flakes and peanut butter.
Mix well and spoon onto waxed paper.

title: hot sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in pot and bring to a slow boil. Simmer over low heat for 1 hour, stirring frequently.
Do not burn!
Serve with little hot dogs.

title: banana frost and flame(yield:  6 generous servings)
directions: Allow ice cream to soften in large mixing bowl; do not melt. Refreeze in an empty milk carton or in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. In a mixing bowl, beat egg whites at high speed with electric mixer.
When eggs begin to stand in peaks, add powdered sugar 1 tablespoon at a time.
Add salt, vanilla and 2 tablespoons rum; continue beating at high speed until whites are stiff.
Cover a bread board with heavy brown paper and arrange 3 banana halves side by side, flat side up.
Place quart block of ice cream on top of bananas and cover with remaining halves flat side down.
Gently spoon egg whites over all until entire ice cream block is sealed. Place bread board in preheated 375° oven for 4 to 5 minutes, keeping a constant eye on the meringue.
Remove as soon as it is a light golden color.
Heat rum in a metal cup.
Slice meringue dessert from bread board into a large silver tray or Pyrex platter and pour rum over it.
Ignite and serve flaming.

title: ham-green bean soup(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Combine ham bone and water in a 6-quart saucepan.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.
Remove meat from bone and cut in chunks.
Add to soup stock along with remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Skim off excess fat.
Just before serving, stir in 1 cup light cream or milk.

title: no bake cookies!!
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in saucepan.
Heat until boiling.
Continue to boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, cocoa, oatmeal, salt and vanilla.
Beat until it thickens.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: "dirty" rice(jambalaya)
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Place rice in saucepan and add broth and bay leaf.
Cover.
Bring to a boil and simmer 15 minutes. Cook bacon.
Cook onions and pepper in bacon drippings until almost brown (add oil if needed).
Add livers; cook until brown. Add garlic and dash of salt and pepper.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump in listed order.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Mix in top of double boiler the egg whites, sugar, water, salt and syrup.
Place over boiling water and beat for 7 minutes; remove from heat.
Add vanilla and beat 1 minute longer.

title: faye's pumpkin pound cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a medium size bowl.
Then add pumpkin and mix again.
Measure and sift flour and remaining ingredients.
Sift again and add to mixture.
Bake in a tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350°
for 35 minutes and then at 275° for 30 minutes.

title: mom's green chile
directions: Save the juice the pork was cooked in or use canned chicken broth with water.
Skim off fat from pork juice.
Add water.
In a deep pot, return pork juice and pork to boil.
Add tomatoes, onion, chile and spices.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: turkey shepherd's pie
directions: Saute onion until transparent.
Add all other ingredients until hot.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish and top with mashed potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in oven until golden brown at 350°.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add water and sugar to Kool-Aid. Sweeten to taste.
Makes about 2 gallons.

title: eastern ky cornbread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: scottish shortbread cookies
directions: Mix flour and butter together with a pastry cutter until mixture looks like coarse sand.
Add sugar and egg.
Work dough with hands into four thick cakes (about 1/4th dough mixture in each).
Roll one cake out with a rolling pin, approximately 1/2 inch thick.
Cut cookies into squares or rectangles.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Prick each cookie with a fork.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: company fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt cube of butter in large iron skillet.
Place flour, salt, pepper and chicken in large grocery sack and shake until chicken is coated completely.
Place chicken in large iron skillet with margarine.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°. Turn chicken one time and bake another 30 minutes.
Chicken will be crispy and golden brown.
Drippings left in skillet make excellent gravy.
Also, chicken will not brown right unless you use an iron skillet.

title: pig pickin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together cake mix, canned oranges with juice, eggs, and oil.
Pour batter into three greased and floured 8 inch round pans.
Layers will be thin.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Cool layers on wire racks.
Mix together whipped topping, drained pineapple, and instant pudding mix.
Fill and frost the cooled cake.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: italian chicken skillet
directions: In 10-inch skillet, cook celery, green pepper, onion and garlic in hot oil until tender.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, chicken, beans, uncooked rice, undrained mushrooms, Italian seasoning, 1/2 teaspoon of salt and 1/8 teaspoon of pepper.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes or until beans and rice are done.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover; cook 2 minutes more or until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry romanoff swizzle
directions: In blender, combine orange juice and berries.
Cover and blend until pureed.
Strain into large pitcher.
Pour carbonated beverages down side of pitcher.
Stir gently.
Serve over ice in tall glasses.
If desired, garnish with fresh strawberries.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mexican chocolate
directions: Heat milk to scalding with the stick of cinnamon and the coffee. Strain and add the chocolate dissolved in the boiling water.
Heat again to the boiling point.
Remove and add the vanilla and salt. Stir and serve hot with whipped cream or marshmallows.

title: sauce for steak
directions: Put oil in bottom of pan.
Cut peppers in quarters or smaller. Slice onion rings and mushrooms.
Add a small amount of salt, pepper or garlic, then add tomato sauce and bake in oven at 300°.

title: oyster chowder
directions: Cook the potatoes in boiling salted water until just cooked but still firm.
Drain, saving the liquid and cook the potato liquid down a little.
Fry salt pork or bacon until brown; remove and add onion to the fat.
Saute until golden and limp; do not allow to brown.
Combine salt pork or bacon, onion, potatoes, potato water, oyster liquor and chopped oysters.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer gently 5 to 10 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper and slowly add cream or milk.
Gently heat the soup just to the boiling point.
Do not boil.
Stir in thyme just before serving and sprinkle the top of each bowl of chowder with a little paprika. Serves 4.

title: apple crisp
directions: Pare apples and slice thin.
Arrange slices in 8-inch round pan.
Combine oatmeal, sugar, flour and cinnamon; cut in margarine.
Sprinkle this mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
(Can use 8-inch square pan.)

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix
crackers,	butter	and
poppy seed.
Press half of this mixture
into casserole dish.
Place chicken over crackers.
Mix soups and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Top with remaining crackers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salmon "party" dip
directions: Place salmon in mixing bowl.
Add sour cream, chili sauce and soup mix.
Stir until well blended.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Stir.
Garnish with red pepper and green herb.
Serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: funnel cake
directions: Preheat 2-inches of cooking oil, or Crisco in a deep skillet at 375 degrees.
Combine ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Stir until batter is smooth.
Use a Funnel with about a 3/8-inch opening. Pour about 1/2 c. batter into Funnel holding your finger over the opening.
Holding about 1-inch over the skillet pour batter in circular design.
Let it brown and turn only once.
Remove from pan, drain, and serve hot with Powdered Sugar or Brown Sugar or even Maple Syrup.

title: fruit casserole
directions: Drain pineapple. Save 6 tablespoons of juice.
Combine sugar, flour
and juice.
Add cheese, pineapple, pears and carrots.
Mix well and place in baking dish. Top with crackers and melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: scottish ham roll
directions: Beat eggs and add to dry ingredients.
Mix well; turn on floured board and knead to form a ball, fairly thick.
Roll up in a floured cloth and tie.
Place on a plate; put in a pot of boiling water and boil 1 1/2 hours.
When ready, turn out and roll on some bread crumbs.
Can be served hot or as a cold sandwich.

title: quick hollandaise chicken
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots in microwave on High for 10 minutes. Meanwhile, brown chicken breasts.
Drain well and place in casserole.
Add vegetables.
Cook Hollandaise sauce according to package directions.
When done, pour over chicken and vegetables and bake until chicken is done, about 1 hour at 375°.

title: hamburger hash chinese style
directions: Brown ground beef in oil in skillet, stirring, until crumbly. Drain.
Add next 7 ingredients and 1 1/2 cups of warm water; mix well.
Put in baking dish.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes, then uncover and bake another 30 minutes.
Top with noodles and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: hot or cold macaroni salad
directions: Amount and choice of vegetables depends on personal taste.
Add or subtract vegetables.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown pork sausage and ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients until melted and well blended.
Spread mixture on party rye slices.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes; 20 to 25 minutes if frozen.
May be prepared ahead of time and frozen.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Place rabbit pieces in stewpot with water, wine, salt and potatoes.
Cook slowly until rabbit can be flaked from the bone with a fork.
Remove rabbit from pot, debone and put meat back in pot.
Add the other ingredients and cook on medium heat, stirring often until vegetables start to break up and lose their identity.

title: mixed fruit punch
directions: Mash bananas and place in blender.
Pour in water and sugar. Blend until smooth.
In a large container, pour blender contents and other juices.
Mix well.
Add the Diet Sprite just before serving.

title: meringue
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, but not too long.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, and beat until it stand in peaks.
Add flavorings and cook in a 350° oven until brown.

title: butterscotch cheesecake squares
directions: In medium saucepan, melt morsels and margarine; stir in crumbs and nuts.
Reserving 1 c. mixture for topping, press remainder firmly onto bottom of a greased 9 inch square pan.
In mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy; beat in Brown Sugar Eagle Brand and eggs. Mix well.
Pour into pan; top with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake 25-30 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool to room temperature; chill before serving.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 9-12 servings.

title: boston bean salad(perfect for a potluck)
directions: In a large bowl combine beans, celery and green onion.
For dressing in a screw-top jar combine vinegar, molasses, oil, mustard and pepper.
Cover and shake well to mix.
Pour dressing over bean mixture.
Stir to coat.
Cover and chill 4 to 24 hours stirring occasionally.

title: veal continental(yields 6 servings)
directions: Cut bacon up in bits.
Saute over medium heat in frypan until golden, not too crisp.
Remove bacon and set aside.
If you have less than 3 tablespoons of drippings, add Puritan oil.

title: white clam sauce
directions: Heat oil and garlic in a skillet until garlic is lightly browned.
Remove from heat.
Add water, parsley and dry seasonings; mix well.
Stir in clams with juice.
Heat thoroughly. Serve hot on cooked spaghetti or macaroni.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: low-fat baked beans
directions: Cut up hot dogs and mix all ingredients.
You may add a little more or less of the seasonings to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: my moms potato soup
directions: In a 4 quart pot, cover potatoes and onions with water; add salt. Bring to a boil; reduce to medium heat and cook until potatoes are well done. (Potatoes should be very soft and soupy.) Remove from heat. Mix the flour and water in a small bowl until smooth and add to potatoes to thicken the mixture. Return to medium heat and stir in margarine and canned milk; then add rest of milk. Stir frequently until soup almost boils. (Do not let it boil.) Remove from heat and add pepper to taste.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Soak gelatine in cold water for 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, lemon juice and salt to beaten egg yolks and cook in double boiler until custard like.
To this, add grated lemon rind and softened gelatine and stir. Cool.
When mixture begins to thicken, fold in beaten egg whites to which the other 1/2 cup of sugar has been added.
Pour into pie shell and cover with whipped cream.
This takes a little more effort than some pies but is worth the work. Serves 6.

title: green bean salad
directions: Blanch green beans 4 to 5 minutes; chill. Chop mint leaves. Add to green beans and set aside. Combine oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and garlic. Add walnuts, red onion and feta cheese to beans. Pour dressing over bean mixture and toss to coat. Chill until ready to serve.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix in order listed, mixing dry ingredients together.
Bake in greased and floured square pan for about 20 or 30 minutes.
Let cake partly cool in pan and then spread on topping.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in milk.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to mix and combine.
Add blueberries.
Pour into greased 8 x 12-inch pan.

title: plain pudding cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, pudding and water.
Add eggs and oil, beating all the time.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Pour into well-greased tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Remove from pan. Prepare a mixture of sugar and juice.
Spoon over cake while hot.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown onion and green pepper in drippings.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce and simmer until liquid is gone.

title: cheesy spinach mushroom casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook spinach and drain liquid into measuring cup.
Reserve spinach for later use.
Add enough water to spinach liquid to make 4 cups.
Place liquid and salt in a medium saucepan and bring to a boil.
Stir in grits slowly. Cover, reduce heat and cook, stirring occasionally, until liquid is absorbed according to grits package directions.
Stir in egg, soup, cheese and spinach.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.
Top with buttered crumbs and bake for 5 more minutes.
Serves 6.

title: drain cleaner
directions: Combine salt and soda.
Pour in drain, followed with a large kettle of boiling water.
Flush with lots of cold water.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook pineapple juice and sugar together until sugar dissolves. Add crushed pineapple and cranberry sauce.
Mix well.
Add nuts. Mix and pour into container and refrigerate until congealed.
Can be served with turkey and other meats.

title: apple bread
directions: Beat sugar, cooking oil, vanilla, eggs and sour cream in large bowl.
Sift flour, cinnamon, soda and nutmeg well in a large bowl. Add to the first mixture.
Add chopped apples and beat well, then add chopped pecans and stir well.
Bake in 2 loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados.
In a bowl, combine avocados, lemon juice, garlic salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
To assemble, spread bean dip in large shallow plate.
Layer with sour cream mixture, then layers of avocado, chopped onions, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Keeps well in refrigerator for several days.

title: sesame shrimp
directions: Combine dressing, soy sauce, lemon juice and garlic powder in mixing bowl.
Add shrimp, stirring to coat.
Set aside.
In medium skillet, heat about 1/2 cup water to boiling over medium-high heat.
Add vegetables.
Cover and steam for 3 minutes. Add shrimp.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook, uncovered, 3 to 5 minutes, until shrimp are warm and vegetables are crisp-tender. Drain off any excess water.
Top with sesame seed.
Serves 4.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Saute onion in bacon grease.
Add diced tomatoes.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar. Beat eggs in milk and add gradually to dry mixture. Add melted butter and blend. Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake at 425° for three minutes. Immediately turn down to 350° and bake for 50 minutes more.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Pour
boiling
water
over Jell-O; stir until mixed and cool. Stir in orange sherbet, marshmallows and oranges.
Whip cream and fold in last.
Chill.

title: fale dunaju(waves of dunaj)
directions: Cream the margarine with sugar and egg yolks until well blended. Add flour, baking powder and lemon juice. Beat egg whites until stiff and add to mixture.
Divide batter into two parts. Add 1.5 teaspoons cocoa and 2 teaspoons water into one part of the batter.
Pour this batter over the first part.
Sprinkle cherries over the top.
Bake at 150° to 200° C for 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. After cake is done, allow to cool and pour Cream over same.

title: hot grilled trout
directions: In a shallow dish, mix lemon juice, butter, olive oil, parsley, sesame seed, Tabasco pepper sauce, ground ginger and salt.
With a fork, pierce skin of brook trout (about 1 pound each).
Coat fish with marinade inside and out.
Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes to an hour.
Place fish in hand held grill; brush with marinade.
Cook about 4-inches from hot coals for 5 minutes.
Turn and brush with marinade.
Cook 5 minutes longer or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together into a large bowl.
Beat eggs, oil and pumpkin in another bowl.
Add to flour mixture and blend well.
Dough will be stiff.
Fold in fruits and nuts.
In a well-greased loaf pan, bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: uncle barb's brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together the first 4 ingredients. Mix separately the butter, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Slowly add flour mixture; beat until smooth.
Spread in a greased deep baking sheet.
Slowly sprinkle walnuts or pecans and chocolate or vanilla chips over.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bar b cups
directions: Brown beef and drain. Stir in sauce and cook over medium heat for 5 to 10 minutes or until heated through. Press biscuit into a muffin tin and shape to fit the bottom and sides. Spoon 2 tablespoons of meat mixture into the center of each cup. Bake at 375° for 15 to 17 minutes or until brown. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 3 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: lazy lemon pie
directions: Mix together lemonade and milk.
Pour into crust.
Top with whipped topping.
Chill.
Can add drops of yellow food coloring to mixture.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake in 350° oven 45 minutes.

title: danish cake
directions: Mix well and
pour
into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Make dirt by crumbling Oreos and vanilla wafers super fine. Combine cream cheese, sugar and margarine.
Mix pudding and milk in separate bowl.
Combine cream cheese mixture and pudding mixture with electric mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: caramels
directions: Mix and cook until hard ball.
Pour into greased pan.
Cool and cut.

title: walnut dressing
directions: In blender or food processor, combine ingredients. Blend until nuts are finely chopped. Cover and chill. Serve with fruit or green salads. Refrigerate leftovers. Makes about 1/2 cup.

title: meat loaf
directions: Make your favorite meat loaf mixture and pat it out on wax paper; top with ham slices and Mozzarella cheese (diced cheese). Roll up like jelly roll with seam on bottom.
Put in baking dish or pan and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes; then take out of oven, sprinkle top of meat loaf with Mozzarella cheese and put back in oven to melt cheese.
Let stand 5 minutes, then slice. This also makes a good sandwich when room temperature.

title: sauteed trout(with fresh tarragon)
directions: In a frying pan large enough to hold both fish, melt butter until nut brown in color (carefully watch so it does not burn). Add fish, tarragon, seasonings and lemon juice and cook on one side for about 3 1/2 minutes.
Turn trout gently with 2 wooden spatulas and continue to cook for about 4 to 5 minutes or until springy when touched and fork shows flesh is flaky.
Remove trout from pan and insert a sharp knife at the back of the trout's head, run knife along the back and underside and the whole bone will be exposed.
Lift tail and it will come off intact with the head. Place fillets on plates and divide sauce from pan.
Serves 2.

title: french scalloped potatoes
directions: Arrange half the potatoes in a buttered casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Top with onions.
Sprinkle with thyme, garlic, salt and pepper.
Mix cream and cornstarch.
Pour evenly over potatoes. Add half of the cheese.
Add remaining potatoes.
Sprinkle on remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until brown. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in baking dish; add corn, whipping cream and salt and pepper.
Blend in flour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until light brown.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Arrange 8 meat balls in casserole. Combine sauce.
Pour over porcupines.
Cover casserole.
Bake one hour at 350°, turning once.

title: kernel corn covering
directions: Mix in blender.
Let set out until warm and soft enough to spread on corn-on-the-cob.

title: orange delight
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill before serving.
May use low-fat cottage cheese, NutraSweet jello and lite Cool Whip to lower calories and fat.
May omit pineapple and increase number of oranges.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crush wafers until consistency of flour.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add milk, wafers, nuts and coconut.
Bake for two hours at 275°.
Cool in pan.
Use tube pan.

title: aunt joey's lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage. Mix in tomatoes and spaghetti sauce. Add basil (sprinkle), 1 bay leaf, oregano, garlic salt and black pepper to taste. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, soup, margarine, the rice and cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Real good.

title: easy red beans and rice
directions: Cook sliced sausage over low heat 5 to 8 minutes.
Add onion, pepper and garlic.
Saute to tender.
Drain, if necessary.
Add beans, tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes. Serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Mix ingredients and bring to boil.
Salt, pepper and flour chicken.
Pour mixture over cut-up chicken pieces.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: sin cake
directions: Bake as directed on cake mix until cake is done.
While still hot, punch hole in cake and pour cream of coconut over cake.
Cool. Top with Cool Whip and 1/2 cup coconut.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Place sauerkraut in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with corned beef, then shredded cheese.
Combine mayonnaise and Thousand Island dressing.
Spread over cheese.
Top with tomato slices. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: candy bar brownies
directions: Melt candy bars and shortening.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; blend well.
Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
While warm, cut into bars.

title: doughnuts
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg.
Sift 4 cups flour with other dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture alternately with milk. Beat well and add rest of flour.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick, cut and fry in deep fat.

title: batengen yaghnee (eggplant stew)
directions: Slice the eggplants and sprinkle them with salt.
Allow them to drain in a colander for at least 1/2 hour.
Fry the onion in 2 tablespoons oil until soft and golden.
Add the meat and brown well.
Add the tomatoes and squash them with a fork.
Stir in the tomato paste and lemon juice and mix thoroughly.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and allspice.
Cover with water, bring to a boil and simmer gently, covered, for about 1 hour.

title: party ryes
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger; drain well.
Melt cheese and seasonings in meat mixture and cool slightly.
Spread over party rye bread.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Can be frozen in layer on cookie sheet and stored in plastic bags.
Thaw at room temperature.

title: savory chicken crescent squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons of the margarine until smooth.
Add the next 5 ingredients; mix well.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforations around edges together to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture onto center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners of dough to top center of chicken mixture; twist slightly and seal edges.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush tops with reserved 1 tablespoon margarine.
Sprinkle with crouton crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: greek tortellini salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine cooked pasta, sweet peppers, onion and olives.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a greased loaf pan until the center is firm, about 40 to 45 minutes.
Slice and serve warm as a main dish or leave in the pan and refrigerate overnight; slice and serve as a cold plate or as a party snack.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind vegetables using coarse blade.
Sprinkle with salt. Let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Heat to boiling, then simmer 3 minutes.
Seal.
Makes 8 to 10 pints.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Soak beans in water in large pot overnight.
Bring to boil and then simmer 1 hour.
Heat oils in large saucepan and saute next 6 ingredients until limp.
Add to cooked beans.
Add next four ingredients and seasonings to soup.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add garbanzo beans, macaroni and zucchini slices. Simmer another 30 minutes.

title: orange blossoms
directions: Melt chocolate chips and add orange juice, nuts and enough crushed vanilla wafers to be able to roll into a ball.
Add more orange juice if mixture is to dry to work.
Roll balls in sugar and store in open container to give a chance to dry up.

title: pecan pie
directions: Whip together with a fork; pour in an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: In skillet, cook onions, pepper and garlic in oil until onions are transparent.
Add the ground beef and fry until mixture gets crumbly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Remove cover the last 15 minutes of cooking.

title: potato and cheese casserole
directions: Place potatoes in large bowl.
Mix soup, milk, margarine, pepper, onion flakes, salt and sour cream in saucepan.
Heat thoroughly, stirring constantly.
Pour over potatoes.
Add half the cheese; mix well.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Yield:
12 servings.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Drain well.
Add Veg-All, V-8 juice, ground beef and corn in crock-pot.
Salt and pepper to taste. This freezes well.

title: oatmeal macaroons
directions: Place shortening, both sugars, vanilla and eggs in bowl and beat thoroughly.
Sift flour with soda.
Add salt and cinnamon. Add to first mixture and mix well.
Fold in oats and nuts.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken ratatouille
directions: You will need one 10 x 13-inch Reynolds oven cooking bag.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, sugar, baking powder and baking soda. Cut in oleo/butter until crumbly.
Beat egg; add buttermilk and raisins to the bowl.
Blend this egg, milk and raisin mixture to the dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Turn onto a floured board and knead several times.
Divide into 2 loaves and place in greased cake pans (8-inch).
Cut 1/2-inch deep cross in top of each loaf. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Best served warm with butter and mint jelly.

title: complete dinner casserole
directions: Brown meat; add onions, bell pepper, chili powder and salt. Cook 5 minutes and drain.
Add tomatoes, beans and rice; stir together.
Spoon into baking dish; top with cheese and olives. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be frozen and cooked layer, if desired.

title: popeye salad
directions: Wash and chop spinach.
Drain bean sprouts and water chestnuts. Slice water chestnuts.
Combine spinach, bean sprouts, water chestnuts, eggs and onions.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
Shake catsup, sugar, oil, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce together in a jar.
At serving time, place vegetables in a large salad bowl or in individual salad bowls.
Spoon dressing over salad and top with bacon bits.
(Or, bacon bits may be added to dressing.)
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: chubby's sugar cookies
directions: Mix well in large bowl.
Add enough flour to roll dough.
Cut and bake at 350°.

title: taco lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix in taco seasoning by directions.
Mix enchilada sauce and taco sauce in bowl.
Dip tortillas in sauce on both sides.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan: tortilla, ground beef, cheese, sour cream and tomatoes.
Do this twice.
Top last tortilla with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Beat
sour
cream, sugar and eggs.
Stir soda and cocoa in hot water; add to sour cream mixture.
Add vanilla.
Mix in flour
and salt.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at
350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Top with favorite chocolate icing.

title: swiss steak
directions: Trim fat.
Cut into 4 serving size pieces.
"Pam" a cold skillet.
Preheat skillet over medium heat.
Brown meat on both sides.
Add the undrained tomatoes (cut up), celery, carrots, onion, water, thyme and pepper.
Bring to boil; reduce heat. Cover and simmer about 1 1/4 hours or until meat is tender. Remove meat from skillet; keep warm.
Cook rice according to directions, omitting butter and salt.
Keep warm.

title: tuna and scallion canape
directions: In mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, except the crackers and pimento.
Blend well.
Place 1 tablespoon of mixture on top of each cracker and garnish with a piece of pimento.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix until well blended.
Store in tightly covered bowl for up to 6 weeks in refrigerator.
When desired, spoon dough from top of bowl into greased muffin tins. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen total.

title: 12 bean soup
directions: Wash and soak beans overnight.
Drain and add next 5 ingredients.
Cover and bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Scald milk and cream.
In a small bowl, combine flour, cornstarch, sugar and salt; mix.
Add to milk and cook 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add egg yolks and cook 1 minute.
Cool.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Pour filling into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Make sure potatoes are very dry.
Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large plastic bag, add all ingredients.
Close bag and shake until potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty potatoes into a shallow pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Garnish, if desired, with chopped parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chipped ham barbecue
directions: Saute onions in oil until transparent; add remaining ingredients and cook on low 30 to 45 minutes, stirring often.
You can also double this and cook in crock-pot on low for 3 to 4 hours.
(You can adjust sugar or vinegar to taste; I like a little more sugar and brown sugar, too.)

title: grape juice
directions: Boil grapes and water hard.
Stir gently and cool.
Don't mash.
Strain.
Add sugar.
Makes 1/2 gallon of juice.
Heat jars and seal.

title: corn meal dumplings
directions: Boil the hock bone until it is very tender.
Mix corn meal and pepper.
Add enough of the boiling broth to make small firm balls of corn meal.
Drop into low boiling broth and let cook slowly for 20 minutes.

title: lasagne(8 to 10 servings)
directions: Brown meat in heavy skillet; spoon off excess fat.
Add garlic, basil, salt, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer, uncovered, about 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Cook lasagne according to package directions.
Drain.
Beat eggs.
Add Ricotta, Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Layer half the lasagne in a buttered 13 1/2 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread with half the Ricotta mixture.
Add half the Mozzarella cheese, then half the meat sauce. Repeat.
Bake in a moderate oven (375°) for 30 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: shipwreck
directions: In skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove to paper towel to drain.
Crumble and set aside.
Brown beef and drain.
Add onion and cook 5 minutes.
Combine ketchup and sugar.
Stir.
Add to beef and beans with bacon all but 2 tablespoons.
Put in pan; top with bacon.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ranch hand muffins
directions: On skillet, heat butter.
Saute ham until heated and beginning to get crispy.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Turn on low.
Cover with lid.
Toast and butter muffins.
Place equal amount of ham and cheese on open face muffin.
Top with taco sauce and sour cream. Serve immediately.

title: apple pie cake(diabetic recipe)
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil, apple pie spice, salt, vanilla and baking soda.
Slowly add flour; fold in apples.
Spread mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Cake is best after being refrigerated for 1 to 2 days.
Serve with caramel topping.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Butter a 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Melt chocolate with water in saucepan over very low heat, stirring until smooth.
Stir in egg yolks; add vanilla.
Beat egg whites, gradually adding sugar until mixture forms stiff peaks.
Stir a small amount into chocolate mixture, then fold chocolate mixture into remaining meringue mixture.
Pour 4 cups into pie plate. Chill remaining mixture.
Bake mixture in pie plate at 350° for 25 minutes or until just set.
Cool slightly, then chill 1 hour. (Center will fall, forming shell.)
Spoon chilled mixture into shell.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Garnish with cranberries and mint.

title: fast fudge
directions: Mix sugar and 1/2 cup water in saucepan.
Boil rapidly for exactly 1 minute.
Pour over peanut butter and vanilla in bowl; beat until thick.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: cheese straws
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Have cheese and butter at room temperature.
Cream together.
Add flour, salt and red pepper powder.
Mix until creamy.
Use small star tip on pastry bag or ribbon disk on cookie press.
Squeeze onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 50 straws.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Clean and chop broccoli.
Add raisins.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Cool and crumble into broccoli and raisin mixture.
Add mayonnaise, sugar and cider vinegar.
Refrigerate.

title: lazy peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Make batter using sugar, milk and flour. Pour this over margarine. Do not stir!!
Pour sweetened peaches over batter. Bake at 350° until done, approximately 1 hour.

title: diablo chili dip
directions: Heat soups over low heat until hot and bubbly, stirring often. Pour into serving dish and top with remaining ingredients.
Serve hot
with tortilla chips or fresh vegetables for dipping.

title: elegant toffee
directions: Combine butter, sugar, vanilla and salt; cook over high heat, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon till butter is melted. Continue 5 to 7 minutes longer or until candy is the color of almonds.
Arrange almonds in a single layer in a 12-inch by 7-inch pan, and pour candy mixture over almonds.
When cool, melt chocolate pieces; dip pieces of candy into the chocolate allowing excess to drip off, then dip into the ground walnuts.

title: beer bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix until moistened.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool before cutting. Makes about 16 slices.

title: good pie dough
directions: Sift flour.
Add sugar and salt; cut in shortening.
Add water and egg gradually to make a soft dough.
Roll out on a lightly floured board for desired size.
Bake at 250° until brown.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli into small pieces.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill overnight.

title: kahlua fruit dip
directions: Pour first 4 ingredients into saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture coats back of spoon; cool.
Fold into whipped cream.
Serve with sliced fresh fruit.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: caramel graham bars
directions: Line a 10 x 15-inch pan with graham crackers.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over graham crackers.
Boil butter, margarine and sugar for 2 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cut along perforated lines in the graham crackers immediately.
Store in tin or airtight container.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens, about 12 minutes.
Add the coconut and chopped nuts.
Beat until frosting is cool and thick enough to spread over cake.

title: chocolate chip cream cheese squares
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Slice one roll of cookies into 24 slices and line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not grease pan!!
Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth with mixer. Spread over layer of cookies.
Slice second roll of cookies into 24 slices and cover cream cheese mixture.
Top with chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix together all ingredients well.
Divide mixture and spread on each tortilla.
Roll tortillas tightly and wrap in Saran Wrap. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Slice each tortilla into 1/2-inch slices.
Serve with salsa.

title: baked zucchini squash
directions: Cut zucchini into halves, lengthwise.
Scoop out seeds.
Line 8 x 11-inch baking pan with aluminum foil.
Place into zucchini halves pinch of seasoned salt, layer of sour cream and layer of grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Sprinkle paprika.
Place zucchini slices, side by side, in pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes (until cheese melts).

title: pecan petites
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Blend in vanilla.
Stir in flour and mix well.
Add nuts and shape rounded teaspoonfuls of dough into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool slightly and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spray a large pizza pan with the cooking spray.
Press out the dough in the pan with hands.
Bake dough at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until browned.
Cool.
Sprinkle with Fruit Fresh.
Beat together the cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled cookie dough.
Arrange fruit on top of cream cheese and Cool Whip mixture.
Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: ham dip
directions: Place all ingredients except cream cheese in a food processor and blend.
Add the cream cheese in small spoonfuls and blend after each addition.
Place in small container and refrigerate.

title: popping barbecups
directions: In a large skillet brown beef.
Drain.
Then add barbecue sauce, sugar and onion.
Set aside.
Place one biscuit in each ungreased muffin cup, pressing dough up sides to edge.
Spoon meat mixture in cups.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine
all ingredients except Swiss cheese.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in
casserole
dish at 350° until lightly brown on top.

title: apricot jello cheese salad
directions: Use only 3 cups water in making the Jell-O.
Let congeal and top with the following:

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve over ice.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line 9-inch pie plate with crust.
Beat eggs until smooth.
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Add sugar, flour, butter and vanilla. Mix well.
Pour into lined pie pan. Bake 1 hour until top is golden brown.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers.
In container with a leakproof lid, mix sugar, oil, vinegar and cheese.
Shake until blended.
Add sliced cucumbers and marinate in refrigerator prior to serving.

title: dump rice
directions: Mix rice, beef consomme and soup together and put in a casserole dish.
Put 4 tablespoons of butter on top of rice mixture.
Lay drained mushrooms on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350 degrees; if juicy, cook longer.

title: bill's sweet potato souffle
directions: Mash the potatoes and stir in all other ingredients.
Spread in a large buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut and cook cabbage until tender.
Grease casserole with margarine.
Layer cabbage, salt and pepper.
Top with sliced cheese and cracker crumbs.
Pour milk over top until all crackers are moist.
Bake at 350° until top of crackers are moistened and brown.

title: whole wheat rolls
directions: Measure sifted white
flour
onto waxed paper.
Soak yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in
warm
water 5 minutes.
Combine milk, sugar and salt in large mixing
bowl.
Stir
to
dissolve.
Beat
in eggs, shortening, yeast and whole
wheat
flour
with
rotary beater
until smooth.
Add remaining flour and mix
until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn out on board and knead until
smooth (5 to 10 minutes).
Place in bowl; grease top and cover with cloth.
Let rise until doubled.
Punch down and let rise again. Shape
into
rolls
as
desired.
Let
rise until doubled. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen rolls.

title: coca-cola cake(from my aunt, helen holm)
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Heat butter, cocoa, Coca-Cola and marshmallows until it boils, watch it closely.
Pour over sugar and flour mixture; mix well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla; beat well.
Pour in greased and floured pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese get to room temperature before making mixture. Make mixture with 1 cup of pecans, using 1 1/2 cups to roll cheese ball in.
This will make 2 cheese balls.

title: brickle dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Use with 6 Granny Smith apples, cut into bite size pieces soaked in pineapple juice.
(Drain before serving.)

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix sugar, flour, milk and vanilla.
Pour into melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Place fruit on top of mixture.
Spices may be added.
Bake, covered, at 350° until browned.

title: steak diane
directions: Combine margarine and Worcestershire sauce in a large nonstick skillet; place over medium heat until hot.
Add mushrooms and onions and saute until tender.

title: stuffing for turkey or chicken
directions: Toast bread on both sides a nice brown.
Split buns and biscuits and toast inside.
Crush all together and moisten with broth from the fowl.
Break eggs into this mixture and stir until well blended.
Season with salt, pepper and sage, according to taste.

title: pie crust no. 1
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients by hand in large bowl.
Work in milk with hand.
Roll out each pie crust on floured board.
Makes 4 crusts.

title: sunflower seed coleslaw
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, onion, salt and pepper together in a small bowl.
Mix well and set aside.
I cut the cabbage into wedges and then into bit size pieces.
Next, pour the dressing mixture over the cabbage.
Add a handful of sunflower seeds (or more, depending on taste) just before serving.

title: parsley potatoes
directions: Peel and cut in 2-inch pieces the potatoes.
In a saucepan, cook potatoes in water to cover until tender.
Drain.
Combine margarine and parsley.
Pour over potatoes and toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Place carrots in a sauce pan with enough water to cover. Cook until tender. In another saucepan, combine brown sugar, cornstarch, orange juice and ginger; stir until smooth. Bring to a boil. Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thick. Add butter. Drain carrots.
Add orange juice mixture to carrots and coat.

title: dreamy italian dressing
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in hot water; cook in top of double boiler over boiling water, stirring, until mixture thickens.
Mix egg yolks (slightly beaten), lemon rind and juice.
Add a little of the hot mixture to them, then gradually stir yolk mixture into the hot mixture.
Add butter; cool.
Turn into a baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff; gradually beat 1/4 cup sugar into them.
Spread meringue over pie; bake in a slow oven at 250° until delicately browned.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix the first 5 ingredients.
In a larger bowl, cream together the margarine, brown sugar, Crisco and sugar. Add the eggs; mix well.
Add flour, vanilla, soda and salt; mix well.
Combine with the first ingredients; mix.
Use 1/4 cup batter for each cookie.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes, or until brown.

title: apple crisp
directions: Make crumbs with flour, sugar and oleo.
Sprinkle on apples and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until apples are done (sugar and cinnamon apples to taste).

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown onion and meat until tender; drain off grease.
Combine all soups, Ro-Tel and taco seasoning with meat.
Add Doritos, breaking into small pieces.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 cup cheese; mix. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake in large, oblong dish (13 x 9-inch) 30 to 45 minutes at 375° to 400°.

title: beef or chuck casserole
directions: Brown beef or chuck and drain.
Cook noodles and drain.
In oblong casserole dish, place one layer of noodles with one layer of beef.
Mix the soups together and spread 1/2 of this mixture over the beef.
Sprinkle over this a little chili powder to taste. Repeat the layers:
one layer of noodles and one layer of beef and spread the remaining soup mixture over this and sprinkle a little more of the chili powder.
Bake at 350° just until hot and melted.

title: raisin pie
directions: Add raisins to water and cook 30 minutes, drain.
Add enough water to juice to make 2 cups.
Combine tapioca, sugar, salt and liquid in saucepan and mix well.
Bring mixture quickly to a full boil over direct heat, stirring constantly and pour small amount of slightly beaten egg, stirring vigorously.
Return to saucepan and bring just to a boil.
Remove from fire.
Add butter, lemon juice and rind to raisin mixture.
Cool slightly before filling shell.
Chill if desired and cover with whipped cream.

title: phoenix hotel pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, salt, butter and vanilla.
Blend well. Add beaten eggs.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: easy greek salad
directions: Combine lettuce, cucumber, tomato, onion and cheese in a large serving bowl. Whisk together oil, lemon juice, oregano and salt in a small bowl. Pour over lettuce mixture ; toss until coated. Serve immediately. Makes 6 servings.

title: *butternut squash filling
directions: Cook squash as per package instructions. Add remaining ingredients and pour into pita dough lined pan.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Place a layer of apples, then bread crumbs and half of sugar in a greased baking dish.
Repeat and sprinkle cinnamon over top. Add 1/4 cup hot water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove cover and brown.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: la cookie elegante
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Stir in vanilla.
Gradually add flour; mix well.
Pat or spread dough evenly over bottom of ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes, or until lightly browned. Cool.
Spread crust with Cream Cheese Topping.
If desired, sprinkle top with almonds.
Continue to bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting into diamonds.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. Sift flour, salt and soda.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla.
Add sour cream and flour alternately, beginning and ending with sour cream.
In a small bowl beat egg whites until stiff moist peaks form when beaters are slowly raised.
Gently fold egg whites into batter.
Turn into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour or until wooden pick inserted comes out clean. Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Turn out on rack to cool completely.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a casserole dish at 350° for one hour.
Stir once after 30 minutes.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Steam the cabbage until tender, but not limp.
Fry the bacon until crisp and set aside.
Saut the onions in the bacon grease. Add the cabbage to the sauted onions; cover and cook until tender on medium heat.
You may need to add a little water depending on the water content of the cabbage.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon. Enjoy!
Serves approximately 8.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Put broccoli in baking dish; sprinkle Minute rice over broccoli.
Pour cream of celery soup over broccoli-rice mixture. Add Velveeta cheese strips over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes covered.

title: cheese ball
directions: Allow cheeses and margarine to soften to room temperature. Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Return mixture to refrigerator to harden slightly.
Roll into 3 equal balls and roll in pecans.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients with the exception of the margarine.
Pour into greased casserole dish and pour melted margarine over the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until the top is lightly browned.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo until limp.
Add celery and bell pepper. Add soups.
Add diced chicken, salsa and sour cream.
Simmer 5 or 10 minutes.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer chips, chicken mixture and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, covered.

title: low-fat good morning muffins
directions: Spray 10 muffin cups with nonstick spray. Set aside.
In a medium bowl, stir together the unbleached flour, whole wheat flour, oat bran, baking powder, cinnamon and allspice.

title: old-time soft sugar cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Cream together butter, sugar, and brown sugar.
Mix in egg, then the buttermilk and vanilla.
Combine the dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Drop mixture by rounded teaspoon 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Combine topping ingredients and sprinkle on top of cookie dough.
Bake at 400° for 7-9 minutes or until set.

title: raspberry and white chocolate bars
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Add 2 cups vanilla chips but do not stir mixture.
Set aside to cool.
Beat eggs until foamy. Gradually add sugar, beating until lemon color.
Stir in butter and chip mixture.
Add 2 cups flour, salt, almond extract and mix on low speed.
Spread half of the batter in a greased and floured 9X13 pan.
Set other half of batter aside.
Bake at 325 degrees for 15-20 minutes, until golden.
Stir 2 cups vanilla chips into remaining batter.
Melt raspberry preserves and spread over cooked layer.
Spread remaining uncooked batter over preserves and sprinkle with sliced almonds.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt butter and chocolate, remove from heat.
Stir in sugar; blend in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour and nuts; mix well.
Spread in greased 8x8 inch pan and bake for 30 minutes.
Be careful not to overbake.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Dice vegetables and mix together.
Mix salad dressing and seasoning.
Pour over spaghetti and mix.
Refrigerate.
Will keep up to a week.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Do not peel orange or lemon.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add all dry ingredients with milk. Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured tube cake pan at 325 for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: gelatin cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, gelatin, eggs and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll in balls; place 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Dip the bottom of a glass jar in sugar and flatten each cookie.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: baked macaroni with four cheeses(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until barely tender, following package directions; drain, reserving 1/2 cup cooking water.
Place macaroni in buttered baking dish.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix Mozzarella,
Cheddar and Swiss cheese together.
Add cheese mixture to hot macaroni; toss lightly.
Mix buttered reserved hot cooking water together; pour over macaroni.
Sprinkle macaroni with grated Romano or Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes. Remove from heat and serve.

title: fast energy drink
directions: In a microwave, cook the carrots in the water until tender. Save the juice.
Cook cabbage until done.
In a blender, combine the cabbage, carrots and juice from carrots.
Blend until ingredients become a drinking consistency.
Salt to taste.

title: graham cracker pie crust
directions: Mix
crumbs and sugar.	Stir into melted butter and mix well. Press
firmly
on
bottom
and sides of 9-inch pie pan. Chill 1 hour or bake in moderate oven at 375° for 7 minutes.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, cinnamon, salt, baking powder and nuts in bowl; set aside.
Beat together until creamy the eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add coconut if desired.
Add and stir dry ingredients from first bowl until moist.
Spoon into greased and floured mini pans.
Bake at 350° (5 to 6 mini pans) for 45 minutes.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Mix together butter and flour.
Press on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let it cool.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheesecake divine
directions: Place graham crackers between 2 pieces of wax paper.
Crush with rolling pin. Mix with 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 cup butter.
Line bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan with this mixture. Bake 10 minutes in preheated 400° oven.
Cool.

title: good morning protein shake
directions: In blender begin with crushed ice and orange juice.
Slowly add 1/2 container of yogurt, then one scoop of protein powder. Mix until well blended.
Add 5 to 6 strawberries and 1/2 banana. Continue to mix until all ingredients are well blended and frothy. Spoon into cup.
Serve with straw and enjoy.

title: orange date bars
directions: Put half of this batter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread filling on this and then add rest of batter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. When bars are cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: onions baked in cream
directions: Separate the sliced onions into rings and put into greased crock-pot.
Sprinkle onions with salt and pepper and half the crushed crackers.
Add cream and dot with butter.
Sprinkle remaining crushed crackers over top.
Top with cheese slices. Cover and cook on high 1 hour, then low 2 to 4 hours.

title: oyster stuffing
directions: Cook onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Add oysters and cook until edges begin to curl.
(I chop the oysters.)
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Makes 2 cups stuffing, enough for a 4 pound fish or chicken.

title: minute penuche frosting
directions: Place in saucepan brown sugar, milk, shortening and salt. Bring slowly to full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Add vanilla and beat until thick enough to spread.
If frosting becomes too thick, thin with 1 tablespoon cream.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Break lettuce into 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Top with desired amounts of green onion, green peppers and celery.
Layer package of cooked green peas.
Mix Miracle Whip and sugar.
Spread this on top of peas.
Sprinkle crisp (broken in small pieces) bacon on mayonnaise mixture.
Then add cheese over top.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Mix before serving.

title: beautiful butterflied shrimp
directions: Shell and clean shrimp.
Split down the back to butterfly, leaving tails on.
Make batter by combining remaining ingredients. Dip shrimp in batter, a few at a time.
Cook in deep fryer of hot oil at 375° for 3 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix well and pour into an unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: mama's crock-pot bean bake
directions: Brown ground chuck in skillet; drain off fat and put beef in crock-pot.
Brown bacon and onions; add with remaining ingredients to crock-pot.
Stir together well.
Cover and cook on low 4 to 8 hours.
Great with cornbread!

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Thaw hash browns. Mix with remaining ingredients and place in greased dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Garnish with bacon bits, if desired.

title: banana nut bread(low-fat)
directions: Combine ingredients, place in loaf pan (greased) and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown and tests clean.

title: ice cream icing
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar well at high speed.
Add flour one tablespoon at a time.
Beat after each.
Add milk and vanilla.
Beat real well.
It will get light and fluffy.

title: easy caramel squares
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
After baked dust with powdered sugar.

title: chocolatey chip cupcakes
directions: Combine cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar; beat until smooth. Add egg, 1/8 teaspoon salt and chocolate chips.
Stir and set aside.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift flour with sugar.
Stir in cornmeal.
Add eggs, milk and oil.
Beat by hand or mixer just until smooth.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheeseburger loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Shape into a loaf.
Put in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour. Top with tomato slices and 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: shrimp or chicken casserole
directions: Saute in 1 stick of butter, celery, bell pepper, onion, garlic, parsley and green onions.
Add rice and shrimp to vegetables.
Add Cheddar cheese soup, mushroom soup, pimentos and black pepper.
Put in 2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Top with toasted bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bread
directions: Put flour in pan plus sugar and salt. Sprinkle yeast on flour. Add water. Mix. While in sticky stage, add oil. Knead on table (floured) about 1/2 hour. Grease a pan about 3 times larger than the dough. Place dough in the pan. Cover and let rise about 2 to 3 hours. Punch down. Grease bread pans. Form the dough; place in bread pans. Let rise again 1 to 2 hours. Bake at 375° until nicely browned.

title: easy fantasy fudge
directions: Lightly grease 13 X 9 inch pan with margarine.
Microwave margarine on high for 1 minute.
Add sugar and milk.
Stir well. Microwave on high for 5 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes.
Stir. Microwave on high 5 1/2 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes.
Stir. Gradually stir in chips until melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place coconut and nuts in pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix softened margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Pour over top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: snow white fruit cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar until real fluffy. Add other ingredients in order given. Beat egg whites until real fluffy, but not dry. Beat in last. Bake 1 hour in slow oven (325°) for 10 minutes. Before cake is done, glaze with white simple syrup and decorate with mixed glazed fruit.

title: spinach spread
directions: Combine all ingredients. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Serve in hollowed out red cabbage or round bread loaf.
Serve with crackers.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Can substitute strawberry or blueberry pie filling in place of cherry.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and let it sit in fridge overnight.

title: butterfinger pie
directions: Mix candy evenly into a bowl of large Cool Whip.
Place in a baked pie shell and chill.
Serve.

title: amazing crock-pot pizza
directions: Saute ground chuck and onion. In a crock-pot, make three layers of ingredients with meat on bottom to cheese on top. Slow cook for 5 hours.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Mix brown sugar and butter.
Pour in bottom of cake pan. Place pineapple slices in this mixture.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt together.
Mix butter, white sugar, egg and vanilla together.
Alternately mix flour mixture and milk into egg mixture.
Pour carefully on top of sauce already in pan.
Bake at 350° until cake is done.
Remove from oven and turn over on cake serving dish.
Let cool.
A round 9-inch pan is good to use.

title: chocolate crazy cake(do not grease or flour pan!)
directions: Mix in 11 x 13-inch pan the first 5 ingredients.
Pour over the oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Add water and stir with a fork. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Do not remove from pan.

title: cracker snack
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except oyster crackers, in large bowl.
Add to oyster crackers and mix.
Let stand 2 hours.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix 1 cup bran and water and let stand 1/2 hour.
Cream together margarine, salt and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add buttermilk and mix.
Add dates, raisins and nuts.
Add flour, baking soda and 2 cups 100% bran and stir until just blended.
Add bran and water mixture.
Stir only to blend.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 24 to 30 muffins.

title: cream cheese braids
directions: Combine scalded sour cream, sugar, butter and salt.
Mix well and let cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl.
Stir in sour cream mixture and eggs.
Gradually stir in flour (dough will be soft).
Cover tightly and chill overnight. Divide dough into 4 equal portions.
Turn each portion out onto a heavily floured board and knead 4 or 5 times.
Roll each into a 12 x 8 inch rectangle.
Spread 1/4 of the filling over each rectangle, leaving a 1/2 inch margin around edges.
Carefully roll up jellyroll fashion, beginning at the long side.
Firmly pinch edge and ends to seal.
Carefully place rolls, seam side down, on greased baking sheets.
Make 6 X-shaped cuts across top of each loaf.
Cover and let rise in a warm place for 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 15-20 minutes.
Spread with glaze while warm.
Yields 4 loaves.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Add softened ice cream and Cool Whip to Oreos and mix in mixer.
Freeze in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex casserole dish.
Take from freezer when ready.
Serves 15.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salmon loaf with cheese sauce
directions: Flake salmon, reserving liquid and remove bones and dark skin. Combine with remaining ingredients. Moisten with salmon liquid. Spoon into a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: blender pesto
directions: Put the garlic in the blender and whirl at high speed. Add the basil, olive oil, nuts and salt and mix until well blended, but still with a bit of texture. Use a spatula to scrape down the sides and blend once more. Check for seasoning. Remove to a jar. Stir in the cheese by hand when ready to add to a dish. Makes about a cup.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into lightly greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with dill weed, Parmesan cheese and garlic salt.
Cover.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: antipasto relish
directions: Cut vegetables in chunks or medium pieces.
Place carrots, beans, celery and cauliflower in salt water brine overnight.
